231static sm_list
232cod_dup_list(sm_list list)
233{
234 sm_list ret_list, new_list = NULL((void*)0);
235 sm_list *last_p = &ret_list;
236 while (list != NULL((void*)0)) {
237 *last_p = new_list = malloc(sizeof(struct list_struct));
238 last_p = &(new_list->next);
239 new_list->node = cod_copy(list->node);
240 list = list->next;
241 }
242 *last_p = NULL((void*)0);
243 return ret_list;
244}

1322/*------------------------------------------------.
1323| Report that the YYRULE is going to be reduced. |
1324`------------------------------------------------*/

1326static void
1327yy_reduce_print (yytype_int16 *yyssp, YYSTYPE *yyvsp, int yyrule)
1328{
1329 unsigned long int yylno = yyrline[yyrule];
1330 int yynrhs = yyr2[yyrule];
1331 int yyi;
1332 YYFPRINTF (stderrstderr, "Reducing stack by rule %d (line %lu):\n",
1333 yyrule - 1, yylno);
1334 /* The symbols being reduced. */
1335 for (yyi = 0; yyi < yynrhs; yyi++)
1336 {
1337 YYFPRINTF (stderrstderr, " $%d = ", yyi + 1);
1338 yy_symbol_print (stderrstderr,
1339 yystos[yyssp[yyi + 1 - yynrhs]],
1340 &(yyvsp[(yyi + 1) - (yynrhs)])
1341 );
1342 YYFPRINTF (stderrstderr, "\n");
1343 }
1344}
1345
1346# define YY_REDUCE_PRINT(Rule) \

1348 if (yydebug) \

1350} while (0)
1351
1352/* Nonzero means print parse trace. It is left uninitialized so that
1353 multiple parsers can coexist. */
1354int yydebug;
1355#else /* !YYDEBUG */
1356# define YYDPRINTF(Args)
1357# define YY_SYMBOL_PRINT(Title, Type, Value, Location)
1358# define YY_STACK_PRINT(Bottom, Top)

1363/* YYINITDEPTH -- initial size of the parser's stacks. */
1364#ifndef YYINITDEPTH200
1365# define YYINITDEPTH200 200

1367
1368/* YYMAXDEPTH -- maximum size the stacks can grow to (effective only
1369 if the built-in stack extension method is used).
1370
1371 Do not make this value too large; the results are undefined if
1372 YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM < YYSTACK_BYTES (YYMAXDEPTH)
1373 evaluated with infinite-precision integer arithmetic. */
1374
1375#ifndef YYMAXDEPTH10000

1380#if YYERROR_VERBOSE0
1381
1382# ifndef yystrlen
1383# if defined __GLIBC__2 && defined _STRING_H1
1384# define yystrlen strlen
1385# else
1386/* Return the length of YYSTR. */
1387static YYSIZE_Tlong unsigned int
1388yystrlen (const char *yystr)
1389{
1390 YYSIZE_Tlong unsigned int yylen;
1391 for (yylen = 0; yystr[yylen]; yylen++)
1392 continue;
1393 return yylen;
1394}
1395# endif
1396# endif
1397
1398# ifndef yystpcpy
1399# if defined __GLIBC__2 && defined _STRING_H1 && defined _GNU_SOURCE
1400# define yystpcpy stpcpy
1401# else
1402/* Copy YYSRC to YYDEST, returning the address of the terminating '\0' in
1403 YYDEST. */
1404static char *
1405yystpcpy (char *yydest, const char *yysrc)
1406{
1407 char *yyd = yydest;
1408 const char *yys = yysrc;
1409
1410 while ((*yyd++ = *yys++) != '\0')
1411 continue;
1412
1413 return yyd - 1;
1414}
1415# endif
1416# endif
1417
1418# ifndef yytnamerr
1419/* Copy to YYRES the contents of YYSTR after stripping away unnecessary
1420 quotes and backslashes, so that it's suitable for yyerror. The
1421 heuristic is that double-quoting is unnecessary unless the string
1422 contains an apostrophe, a comma, or backslash (other than
1423 backslash-backslash). YYSTR is taken from yytname. If YYRES is
1424 null, do not copy; instead, return the length of what the result
1425 would have been. */
1426static YYSIZE_Tlong unsigned int
1427yytnamerr (char *yyres, const char *yystr)
1428{
1429 if (*yystr == '"')
1430 {
1431 YYSIZE_Tlong unsigned int yyn = 0;
1432 char const *yyp = yystr;
1433
1434 for (;;)
1435 switch (*++yyp)
1436 {
1437 case '\'':
1438 case ',':
1439 goto do_not_strip_quotes;
1440
1441 case '\\':
1442 if (*++yyp != '\\')
1443 goto do_not_strip_quotes;
1444 /* Fall through. */
1445 default:
1446 if (yyres)
1447 yyres[yyn] = *yyp;
1448 yyn++;
1449 break;
1450
1451 case '"':
1452 if (yyres)
1453 yyres[yyn] = '\0';
1454 return yyn;
1455 }
1456 do_not_strip_quotes: ;
1457 }
1458
1459 if (! yyres)
1460 return yystrlen (yystr);
1461
1462 return yystpcpy (yyres, yystr) - yyres;
1463}
1464# endif
1465
1466/* Copy into *YYMSG, which is of size *YYMSG_ALLOC, an error message
1467 about the unexpected token YYTOKEN for the state stack whose top is
1468 YYSSP.
1469
1470 Return 0 if *YYMSG was successfully written. Return 1 if *YYMSG is
1471 not large enough to hold the message. In that case, also set
1472 *YYMSG_ALLOC to the required number of bytes. Return 2 if the
1473 required number of bytes is too large to store. */
1474static int
1475yysyntax_error (YYSIZE_Tlong unsigned int *yymsg_alloc, char **yymsg,
1476 yytype_int16 *yyssp, int yytoken)
1477{
1478 YYSIZE_Tlong unsigned int yysize0 = yytnamerr (YY_NULLPTR0, yytname[yytoken]);
1479 YYSIZE_Tlong unsigned int yysize = yysize0;
1480 enum { YYERROR_VERBOSE_ARGS_MAXIMUM = 5 };
1481 /* Internationalized format string. */
1482 const char *yyformat = YY_NULLPTR0;
1483 /* Arguments of yyformat. */
1484 char const *yyarg[YYERROR_VERBOSE_ARGS_MAXIMUM];
1485 /* Number of reported tokens (one for the "unexpected", one per
1486 "expected"). */
1487 int yycount = 0;
1488
1489 /* There are many possibilities here to consider:
1490 - If this state is a consistent state with a default action, then
1491 the only way this function was invoked is if the default action
1492 is an error action. In that case, don't check for expected
1493 tokens because there are none.
1494 - The only way there can be no lookahead present (in yychar) is if
1495 this state is a consistent state with a default action. Thus,
1496 detecting the absence of a lookahead is sufficient to determine
1497 that there is no unexpected or expected token to report. In that
1498 case, just report a simple "syntax error".
1499 - Don't assume there isn't a lookahead just because this state is a
1500 consistent state with a default action. There might have been a
1501 previous inconsistent state, consistent state with a non-default
1502 action, or user semantic action that manipulated yychar.
1503 - Of course, the expected token list depends on states to have
1504 correct lookahead information, and it depends on the parser not
1505 to perform extra reductions after fetching a lookahead from the
1506 scanner and before detecting a syntax error. Thus, state merging
1507 (from LALR or IELR) and default reductions corrupt the expected
1508 token list. However, the list is correct for canonical LR with
1509 one exception: it will still contain any token that will not be
1510 accepted due to an error action in a later state.
1511 */
1512 if (yytoken != YYEMPTY(-2))
1513 {
1514 int yyn = yypact[*yyssp];
1515 yyarg[yycount++] = yytname[yytoken];
1516 if (!yypact_value_is_default (yyn)(!!((yyn) == (-239))))
1517 {
1518 /* Start YYX at -YYN if negative to avoid negative indexes in
1519 YYCHECK. In other words, skip the first -YYN actions for
1520 this state because they are default actions. */

4470static char *
4471copy_line(const char *line_begin)
4472{
4473 const char *line_end;
4474 if ((line_end = strchr(line_begin, 10)) == NULL((void*)0)) {
4475 /* no CR */
4476 return strdup(line_begin);
4477 } else {
4478 char *tmp = malloc(line_end - line_begin + 1);
4479 strncpy(tmp, line_begin, line_end - line_begin);
4480 tmp[line_end - line_begin] = 0;
4481 return tmp;
4482 }
4483}

4490
4491static void
4492print_context(cod_parse_context context, int line, int character)
4493{
4494 const char *tmp = cod_code_string;
4495 const char *line_begin = cod_code_string;
4496 char *line_copy = NULL((void*)0);
4497 int i, line_len, offset = 0;
4498
4499 while (line > 1) {
4500 switch(*tmp) {
4501 case 10:
4502 line_begin = tmp + 1;
4503 line--;
4504 break;
4505 case 0:
4506 line = 1; /* end of src */
4507 break;
4508 }
4509 tmp++;
4510 }
4511 if (character > 40) {
4512 offset = character - 40;
4513 }
4514 line_copy = copy_line(line_begin + offset);
4515 line_len = strlen(line_copy);
4516 if (line_len > 60) {
4517 line_copy[60] = 0;
4518 }
4519 context->error_func(context->client_data, line_copy);
4520 context->error_func(context->client_data, "\n");
4521 free(line_copy);
4522 for(i=offset + 1; i< character; i++) {
4523 if (line_begin[i-1] == '\t') {
4524 context->error_func(context->client_data, "\t");
4525 } else {
4526 context->error_func(context->client_data, " ");
4527 }
4528 }
4529 context->error_func(context->client_data, "^\n");
4530}

4535 char tmp_str[100];
4536 sprintf(tmp_str, "## Error %s\n", str);
4537 yycontext->error_func(yycontext->client_data, tmp_str);
4538 yycontext->error_func(yycontext->client_data, "## While parsing near ");
4539 yycontext->error_func(yycontext->client_data, yytextcod_yytext);
4540 sprintf(tmp_str, ", offset = %d, line = %d ####\n",lex_offset,line_count);
4541 yycontext->error_func(yycontext->client_data, tmp_str);
4542 print_context(yycontext, line_count, lex_offset);
4543 yyerror_count++;
4544}

4824 new_context->defined_types = malloc(sizeof(char*) * (type_count + 2));
4825 for (i=0; i<= type_count; i++) {
4826 new_context->defined_types[i] = context->defined_types[i];
4827 }
4828 return new_context;
4829}
4830
4831static sm_ref
4832find_containing_iterator(scope_ptr scope)
4833{
4834 if (scope == NULL((void*)0)) return NULL((void*)0);
4835 if ((scope->code_container != NULL((void*)0)) &&
4836 (scope->code_container->node_type == cod_iteration_statement)) {
4837 return scope->code_container;
4838 }
4839 return find_containing_iterator(scope->containing_scope);
4840}
4841
4842static void *
4843resolve_extern(char *id, scope_ptr scope)
4844{
4845 if (scope == NULL((void*)0)) return NULL((void*)0);
4846 if (scope->externs != NULL((void*)0)) {
4847 cod_extern_list externs = scope->externs;
4848 while(externs->extern_name != NULL((void*)0)) {
4849 if (strcmp(id, externs->extern_name) == 0) {
4850 return externs->extern_value;
4851 }
4852 externs++;
4853 }
4854 }
4855 return resolve_extern(id, scope->containing_scope);
4856}

4858static scope_ptr
4859push_scope_container(scope_ptr containing_scope, sm_ref container)
4860{
4861 scope_ptr new_scope = malloc(sizeof(*new_scope));
4862 new_scope->externs = NULL((void*)0);
4863 new_scope->entry_list = NULL((void*)0);
4864 new_scope->code_container = container;
4865 new_scope->containing_scope = containing_scope;
4866 return new_scope;
4867}

4869static scope_ptr
4870push_scope(scope_ptr containing_scope)
4871{
4872 scope_ptr new_scope = malloc(sizeof(*new_scope));
4873 new_scope->externs = NULL((void*)0);
4874 new_scope->entry_list = NULL((void*)0);
4875 new_scope->code_container = NULL((void*)0);
4876 new_scope->containing_scope = containing_scope;
4877 return new_scope;
4878}
4879
4880static void
4881pop_scope(scope_ptr scope)
4882{
4883 st_entry list = scope->entry_list;
4884 while (list != NULL((void*)0)) {
4885 st_entry tmp = list->next;
4886 free(list);
4887 list = tmp;
4888 }
4889 free(scope);
4890}
4891
4892extern void
4893dump_scope(scope_ptr scope)
4894{
4895 printf("Containing_scope is %p\n", scope->containing_scope);
4896 printf("Extern list:");
4897 if (scope->externs != NULL((void*)0)) {
4898 int i = 0;
4899 while (scope->externs[i].extern_name != NULL((void*)0)) {
4900 printf("\t\"%s\" -> 0x%p\n", scope->externs[i].extern_name,
4901 scope->externs[i].extern_value);
4902 i++;
4903 }
4904 }
4905 printf("Symbol list:");
4906 if (scope->entry_list != NULL((void*)0)) {
4907 st_entry e = scope->entry_list;
4908 while (e != NULL((void*)0)) {
4909 printf("\t\"%s\" -> 0x%p [%s]\n", e->id, e->node, namespace_str[e->ns]);
4910 cod_print(e->node);
4911 e = e->next;
4912 }
4913 }

4943static sm_ref
4944resolve_local(char *id, scope_ptr scope)
4945{
4946 st_entry list = scope->entry_list;
4947 while(list != NULL((void*)0)) {
4948 if (strcmp(list->id, id) == 0) {
4949 return list->node;
4950 }
4951 list = list->next;
4952 }
4953 return NULL((void*)0);
4954}
4955
4956static sm_ref
4957resolve(char *id, scope_ptr scope)
4958{
4959 sm_ref tmp;
4960 if (scope == NULL((void*)0)) return NULL((void*)0);
4961 tmp = resolve_local(id, scope);
4962 if (tmp != NULL((void*)0)) {
4963 return tmp;
4964 }
4965 return resolve(id, scope->containing_scope);
4966}
4967
4968static int
4969determine_unary_type(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref expr, sm_ref right)
4970{
4971 int right_type = cod_sm_get_type(right);
4972 operator_t op = expr->node.operator.op;
4973 switch(right_type) {
4974 case DILL_C: case DILL_UC: case DILL_S: case DILL_US:
4975 right_type = DILL_I; /* integer promotion */
4976 }
4977 if (op == op_minus) {
4978 switch(right_type) {
4979 case DILL_U:
4980 return DILL_I;
4981 case DILL_UL:
4982 return DILL_L;
4983 }
4984 }
4985 return right_type;
4986}
4987
4988static int
4989determine_op_type(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref expr,
4990 sm_ref left, sm_ref right)
4991{
4992 int unsigned_used = 0;
4993 int left_type = cod_sm_get_type(left);
4994 int right_type = cod_sm_get_type(right);
4995 operator_t op = expr->node.operator.op;
4996
4997 if (left_type == DILL_P) {
4998 sm_ref ctype;
4999 if (is_string(expr->node.operator.left) &&
5000 is_string(expr->node.operator.right) &&
5001 (op == op_eq)) {
5002 return DILL_I;
5003 }
5004
5005 ctype = get_complex_type(context, left);
5006 if(ctype && (ctype->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl)) {
5007 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5008 "Illegal arithmetic. Left side is a structure.");
5009 return DILL_ERR;
5010 }
5011
5012 switch(right_type) {
5013 case DILL_P:
5014 case DILL_C:
5015 case DILL_UC:
5016 case DILL_S:
5017 case DILL_US:
5018 case DILL_I:
5019 case DILL_U:
5020 case DILL_L:
5021 case DILL_UL:
5022 case DILL_B:
5023 return DILL_P;
5024
5025 default:
5026 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5027 "Illegal pointer arithmetic. Right side is of incompatible type.");
5028 return DILL_ERR;
5029 }
5030 }
5031 if (right_type == DILL_P) {
5032 sm_ref right_complex = get_complex_type(context, right);
5033 if(right_complex && (right->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl)) {
5034 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5035 "Illegal arithmetic. Right side is a structure.");
5036 return DILL_ERR;
5037 }
5038
5039 switch(left_type) {
5040 case DILL_P:
5041 case DILL_C:
5042 case DILL_UC:
5043 case DILL_S:
5044 case DILL_US:
5045 case DILL_I:
5046 case DILL_U:
5047 case DILL_L:
5048 case DILL_UL:
5049 return DILL_P;
5050
5051 default:
5052 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5053 "Illegal pointer arithmetic. Left side is of incompatible type.");
5054 return DILL_ERR;
5055 }
5056
5057 }
5058 if (left_type == DILL_B) {
5059 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5060 "Illegal arithmetic. Left side is a structured type");
5061 return DILL_ERR;
5062 }
5063 if (right_type == DILL_B) {
5064 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5065 "Illegal arithmetic. Right side is a structured type");
5066 return DILL_ERR;
5067 }
5068 if ((left_type == DILL_D) || (right_type == DILL_D)) {
5069 if ((op == op_modulus) || (op == op_log_or) || (op == op_log_and)) {
5070 cod_src_error(context, expr, "Operands must be integral.");
5071 return DILL_ERR;
5072 } else {
5073 return DILL_D;
5074 }
5075 }
5076 if ((left_type == DILL_F) || (right_type == DILL_F)) {
5077 if ((op == op_modulus) || (op == op_log_or) || (op == op_log_and)) {
5078 cod_src_error(context, expr, "Operands must be integral.");
5079 return DILL_ERR;
5080
5081 } else {
5082 return DILL_F;
5083 }
5084 }
5085 switch(left_type) {
5086 case DILL_C: case DILL_UC: case DILL_S: case DILL_US:
5087 left_type = DILL_I; /* integer promotion */
5088 }
5089 switch(right_type) {
5090 case DILL_C: case DILL_UC: case DILL_S: case DILL_US:
5091 right_type = DILL_I; /* integer promotion */
5092 }
5093 switch(left_type) {
5094 case DILL_UC: case DILL_US: case DILL_U: case DILL_UL:
5095 unsigned_used++;
5096 }
5097 switch(right_type) {
5098 case DILL_UC: case DILL_US: case DILL_U: case DILL_UL:
5099 unsigned_used++;
5100 }
5101 if ((op == op_left_shift) || (op == op_right_shift)) return left_type;
5102 if ((left_type == DILL_UL) || (right_type == DILL_UL)) return DILL_UL;
5103 if ((left_type == DILL_L) || (right_type == DILL_L)) {
5104 /* GSE -bug This test should be for *generated* target, not host */
5105 if (sizeof(long) > sizeof(unsigned int)) {
5106 /* Long can represent all values of unsigned int */
5107 return DILL_L;
5108 } else {
5109 return unsigned_used? DILL_UL : DILL_L;
5110 }
5111 }
5112 if ((left_type == DILL_U) || (right_type == DILL_U)) return DILL_U;
5113 return unsigned_used? DILL_U: DILL_I;
5114}

5122static int
5123is_n_dimen_array(int dimen, sm_ref expr)
5124{
5125 if ((dimen == 0) && (expr == NULL((void*)0))) return 1;
5126 if ((dimen > 0) && (expr == NULL((void*)0))) return 0;
5127 if (dimen == 0) {
5128 if (expr->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
5129 return 0;
5130 } else {
5131 return 1;
5132 }
5133 }
5134 if (expr->node_type == cod_field_ref) {
5135 return is_n_dimen_array(dimen, expr->node.field_ref.sm_field_ref);
5136 }
5137 if (expr->node_type == cod_element_ref) {
5138 return is_n_dimen_array(dimen + 1, expr);
5139 }
5140 if (expr->node_type != cod_field) return 0;
5141 if (expr->node_type == cod_field) {
5142 return is_n_dimen_array(dimen, expr->node.field.sm_complex_type);
5143 }
5144 /* ought to recurse or handle above */
5145 assert(0)((void) sizeof ((0) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (0) ; else __assert_fail
("0", "cod/cod.y", 2880, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__);
}));
5146 return 0;
5147}
5148
5149static int
5150is_string(sm_ref expr)
5151{
5152 if (expr->node_type == cod_field) {
5153 return (expr->node.field.string_type && (strcmp(expr->node.field.string_type, "string") == 0));
5154 } else if (expr->node_type == cod_field_ref) {
5155 return is_string(expr->node.field_ref.sm_field_ref);
5156 } else if (expr->node_type == cod_identifier) {
5157 return is_string(expr->node.identifier.sm_declaration);
5158 } else if (expr->node_type == cod_conditional_operator) {
5159 return is_string(expr->node.conditional_operator.e1); /* e2 must be similar */
5160 } else if (expr->node_type == cod_declaration) {
5161 if (expr->node.declaration.cg_type != DILL_P) return 0;
5162 if (expr->node.declaration.sm_complex_type != NULL((void*)0)) return 0;
5163 /* only strings have pointers without complex types */
5164 return 1;
5165 } else if (expr->node_type == cod_constant) {
5166 return (expr->node.constant.token == string_constant);
5167 }
5168 return 0;
5169}
5170
5171static int
5172is_const(sm_ref expr)
5173{
5174 switch(expr->node_type) {
5175 case cod_field_ref:
5176 return is_const(expr->node.field_ref.struct_ref);
5177 case cod_element_ref:
5178 return is_const(expr->node.element_ref.array_ref);
5179 case cod_cast:
5180 return is_const(expr->node.cast.expression);
5181 case cod_identifier:
5182 return is_const(expr->node.identifier.sm_declaration);
5183 case cod_declaration:
5184 return expr->node.declaration.const_var;
5185 case cod_constant:
5186 return 1;
5187 case cod_operator:
5188 /* most operator errors handled elsewhere. Here we're only looking for dereference */
5189 if (expr->node.operator.op == op_deref) {
5190 return is_const(expr->node.operator.right);
5191 }
5192 return 0;
5193 default:
5194 printf("Unhandled case in is_const()\n");
5195 cod_print(expr);
5196 assert(0)((void) sizeof ((0) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (0) ; else __assert_fail
("0", "cod/cod.y", 2931, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__);
}));
5197 }
5198 return 0;
5199}
5200
5201extern int
5202cod_expr_is_string(sm_ref expr)
5203{
5204 return is_string(expr);
5205}
5206
5207extern int
5208is_control_value(sm_ref expr, sm_ref strct)
5209{
5210 sm_list fields;
5211 if (expr->node_type == cod_field_ref) {
5212 return is_control_value(expr->node.field_ref.sm_field_ref,
5213 expr->node.field_ref.struct_ref);
5214 }
5215 if (expr->node_type != cod_field) return 0;
5216 assert(strct != NULL)((void) sizeof ((strct != ((void*)0)) ? 1 : 0), __extension__
({ if (strct != ((void*)0)) ; else __assert_fail ("strct != NULL"
, "cod/cod.y", 2951, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
5217 strct = get_complex_type(0, strct);
5218 if (strct->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
5219 strct = strct->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
5220 }
5221 if (strct->node_type == cod_declaration) {
5222 strct = strct->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
5223 }
5224 assert(strct->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl)((void) sizeof ((strct->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl)
? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (strct->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl
) ; else __assert_fail ("strct->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl"
, "cod/cod.y", 2959, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
5225 fields = strct->node.struct_type_decl.fields;
5226 while(fields != NULL((void*)0)) {
5227 sm_ref ctype = fields->node->node.field.sm_complex_type;
5228 if ((ctype != NULL((void*)0)) && (ctype->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl))
5229 ctype = ctype->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
5230 while (ctype != NULL((void*)0)) {
5231 if (ctype->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
5232 if (ctype->node.array_type_decl.sm_dynamic_size == expr) {
5233 return 1;
5234 }
5235 ctype = ctype->node.array_type_decl.sm_complex_element_type;
5236 } else {
5237 ctype = NULL((void*)0);
5238 }
5239 }
5240 fields = fields->next;
5241 }
5242 return 0;
5243}

5246#define FALSE0 0
5247#endif
5248
5249static char*
5250type_list_to_string(cod_parse_context context, sm_list type_list, int *size)
5251{
5252 sm_list orig_list = type_list;
5253 int short_appeared = 0;
5254 int long_appeared = 0;
5255 int long_long_appeared = 0;
5256 int int_appeared = 0;
5257 int double_appeared = 0;
5258 int float_appeared = 0;
5259 int char_appeared = 0;
5260 int signed_appeared = 0;
5261 int unsigned_appeared = 0;
5262 int void_appeared = 0;
5263 int string_appeared = 0;
5264 int spec_count = 0;
5265 int prefix_end = 0;
5266 int type_found = 0;
5267 int cg_type;
5268
5269 cg_type = DILL_ERR;
5270 while ((type_list != NULL((void*)0)) && (prefix_end == 0)) {
5271 sm_ref node = type_list->node;
5272 int typ = -1;
5273 if (node->node_type == cod_type_specifier) {
5274 typ = type_list->node->node.type_specifier.token;
5275 if ((typ == STAR) || (typ == AT)) {
5276 prefix_end = 1;
5277 type_list = type_list->next;
5278 continue;
5279 }
5280 }
5281 if (node->node_type != cod_type_specifier) {
5282 if (node->node_type == cod_identifier) {
5283 return NULL((void*)0);
5284 } else if (node->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl) {
5285 return NULL((void*)0);
5286 } else {
5287 printf("Unknown node type in type_list_to_string\n");
5288 break;
5289 }
5290 } else {
5291 spec_count++;
5292 switch (typ) {
5293 case INT:
5294 int_appeared++;
5295 break;
5296 case LONG:
5297 long_appeared++;
5298 break;
5299 case SHORT:
5300 short_appeared++;
5301 break;
5302 case DOUBLE:
5303 double_appeared++;
5304 break;
5305 case STRING:
5306 string_appeared++;
5307 break;
5308 case VOID:
5309 void_appeared++;
5310 break;
5311 case FLOAT:
5312 float_appeared++;
5313 break;
5314 case CHAR:
5315 char_appeared++;
5316 break;
5317 case SIGNED:
5318 signed_appeared++;
5319 break;
5320 case UNSIGNED:
5321 unsigned_appeared++;
5322 break;
5323 case TYPEDEF:
5324 spec_count--;
5325 break;
5326 case STATIC:
5327 spec_count--;
5328 break;
5329 case EXTERN_TOKEN:
5330 spec_count--;
5331 break;
5332 case CONST:
5333 spec_count--;
5334 break;
5335 default:
5336 printf("Unknown type\n");
5337 }
5338 type_list = type_list->next;
5339 }
5340 }
5341 if (spec_count == 0) {
5342 if (type_list == NULL((void*)0)) cg_type = DILL_I; /* default to int */
5343 goto finalize;
5344 }
5345 if (void_appeared && (spec_count > 1)) {
5346 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node,
5347 "Void type may not appear with other specifiers");
5348 cg_type = DILL_ERR;
5349 return NULL((void*)0);
5350 }
5351 if (string_appeared && (spec_count > 1)) {
5352 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node,
5353 "String type may not appear with other specifiers");
5354 cg_type = DILL_ERR;
5355 return NULL((void*)0);
5356 }
5357 if (void_appeared) {
5358 cg_type = DILL_V;
5359 goto finalize;
5360 }
5361 if (string_appeared) {
5362 cg_type = DILL_P;
5363 goto finalize;
5364 }
5365 if (short_appeared && long_appeared) {
5366 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node,
5367 "Only one of long or short permitted");
5368 cg_type = DILL_ERR;
5369 return NULL((void*)0);
5370 }
5371 if (short_appeared && (double_appeared + float_appeared)) {
5372 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node,
5373 "Short may not be specified with double or float");
5374 cg_type = DILL_ERR;
5375 return NULL((void*)0);
5376 }
5377 if (double_appeared + float_appeared) {
5378 if (double_appeared + float_appeared + short_appeared + signed_appeared + unsigned_appeared + char_appeared + int_appeared > 1) {
5379 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node, "Bad type spec");
5380 cg_type = DILL_ERR;
5381 return NULL((void*)0);
5382 } else {
5383 /* not handling LONG plus one of these */
5384 if (double_appeared) {
5385 cg_type = DILL_D;
5386 goto finalize;
5387 } else {
5388 cg_type = DILL_F;
5389 goto finalize;
5390 }
5391 }
5392 }
5393
5394 /* neither float or double appeared */
5395 if (long_appeared == 2) {
5396 long_long_appeared++;
5397 long_appeared = 0;
5398 }
5399 if (short_appeared + char_appeared + long_appeared + long_long_appeared >= 2) {
5400 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node,
5401 "Only one integer size spec may be specified");
5402 cg_type = DILL_ERR;
5403 return NULL((void*)0);
5404 }
5405 if (unsigned_appeared + signed_appeared > 1) {
5406 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node, "Bad type spec");
5407 cg_type = DILL_ERR;
5408 return NULL((void*)0);
5409 }
5410 if (unsigned_appeared) {
5411 if (char_appeared) {
5412 cg_type = DILL_UC;
5413 goto finalize;
5414 } else if (short_appeared) {
5415 cg_type = DILL_US;
5416 goto finalize;
5417 } else if (long_appeared || long_long_appeared) {
5418 cg_type = DILL_UL;
5419 goto finalize;
5420 } else {
5421 cg_type = DILL_U;
5422 goto finalize;
5423 }
5424 } else {
5425 if (char_appeared) {
5426 cg_type = DILL_C;
5427 goto finalize;
5428 } else if (short_appeared) {
5429 cg_type = DILL_S;
5430 goto finalize;
5431 } else if (long_appeared || long_long_appeared) {
5432 cg_type = DILL_L;
5433 goto finalize;
5434 } else {
5435 cg_type = DILL_I;
5436 goto finalize;
5437 }
5438 }
5439 finalize:
5440 if (cg_type != DILL_ERR) {
5441 type_found++;
5442 }
5443 switch(cg_type) {
5444 case DILL_C:
5445 *size = sizeof(char);
5446 return strdup("integer");
5447 case DILL_UC:
5448 *size = sizeof(char);
5449 return strdup("unsigned integer");
5450 case DILL_I:
5451 *size = sizeof(int);
5452 return strdup("integer");
5453 case DILL_L:
5454 *size = sizeof(long);
5455 return strdup("integer");
5456 case DILL_S:
5457 *size = sizeof(short);
5458 return strdup("integer");
5459 case DILL_U:
5460 *size = sizeof(int);
5461 return strdup("unsigned integer");
5462 case DILL_UL:
5463 *size = sizeof(long);
5464 return strdup("unsigned integer");
5465 case DILL_US:
5466 *size = sizeof(short);
5467 return strdup("unsigned integer");
5468 case DILL_F:
5469 *size = sizeof(float);
5470 return strdup("float");
5471 case DILL_D:
5472 *size = sizeof(double);
5473 return strdup("float");
5474 }
5475 return NULL((void*)0);
5476}
5477
5478static sm_ref
5479cod_build_parsed_type_node(cod_parse_context c, char *name, sm_list l)
5480{
5481 sm_ref decl = cod_new_struct_type_decl();
5482 sm_list *end_ptr = &decl->node.struct_type_decl.fields;
5483
5484 sm_list tmp = l;
5485 sm_list last_type = NULL((void*)0);
5486 int field_count = 0;
5487 decl->node.struct_type_decl.id = name;
5488
5489 while(tmp != NULL((void*)0)) {
5490 sm_ref node = tmp->node;
5491 sm_list typ = NULL((void*)0);
5492 sm_list new_elem;
5493 new_elem = malloc(sizeof(*new_elem));
5494 new_elem->next = NULL((void*)0);
5495 new_elem->node = cod_new_field();
5496 if (node->node_type == cod_declaration) {
5497 typ = cod_dup_list(node->node.declaration.type_spec);
5498 new_elem->node->node.field.name = strdup(node->node.declaration.id);
5499 new_elem->node->node.field.string_type =
5500 type_list_to_string(c, typ, &new_elem->node->node.field.cg_size);
5501 } else if (node->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
5502 sm_ref base_decl = node->node.array_type_decl.element_ref;
5503 sm_ref size = node->node.array_type_decl.size_expr;
5504 char *base_string_type = NULL((void*)0);
5505 char *size_str = NULL((void*)0), *final_type;
5506 typ = cod_dup_list(node->node.array_type_decl.type_spec);
5507 if (base_decl->node_type != cod_declaration) {
5508 printf("Array base type must be a simple type\n");
5509 return NULL((void*)0);
5510 }
5511 new_elem->node->node.field.name = strdup(base_decl->node.declaration.id);
5512 base_string_type =
5513 type_list_to_string(c, typ, &new_elem->node->node.field.cg_size);
5514 if (size->node_type == cod_identifier) {
5515 size_str = size->node.identifier.id;
5516 } else {
5517 int free_val = 0;
5518 sm_ref constant = evaluate_constant_return_expr(c, size, &free_val);
5519 if (constant->node_type == cod_constant) {
5520 if (constant->node.constant.token != integer_constant) {
5521 printf("Array size constant is non-integer\n");
5522 return NULL((void*)0);
5523 } else {
5524 size_str = constant->node.constant.const_val;
5525 }
5526 if (free_val) free(constant);
5527 } else {
5528 printf("Unexpected value for array size\n");
5529 return NULL((void*)0);
5530 }
5531 }
5532 if (base_string_type) {
5533 final_type = malloc(strlen(base_string_type) +
5534 strlen(size_str) + 3);
5535 sprintf(final_type, "%s[%s]", base_string_type, size_str);
5536 new_elem->node->node.field.string_type = final_type;
5537 free(base_string_type);
5538 } else {
5539 new_elem->node->node.field.string_type = NULL((void*)0);
5540 }
5541 }
5542 new_elem->node->node.field.cg_offset = -1;
5543 new_elem->node->node.field.cg_type = DILL_ERR;
5544 new_elem->node->node.field.type_spec = typ;
5545 cod_rfree(node);
5546 field_count++;
5547 last_type = tmp;
5548 tmp = tmp->next;
5549 free(last_type);
5550 *end_ptr = new_elem;
5551 end_ptr = &new_elem->next;
5552 }
5553 return decl;
5554}
5555
5556int
5557is_array(sm_ref expr)
5558{
5559 sm_ref typ;
5560 if (expr->node_type == cod_field_ref) {
5561 return is_array(expr->node.field_ref.sm_field_ref);
5562 }
5563 if (expr->node_type == cod_identifier) {
5564 return is_array(expr->node.identifier.sm_declaration);
5565 }
5566 if (expr->node_type == cod_declaration) {
5567 sm_ref ctype = expr->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
5568 if ((ctype != NULL((void*)0)) && (ctype->node_type == cod_array_type_decl)) {
5569 return 1;
5570 }
5571 }
5572 typ = get_complex_type(NULL((void*)0), expr);
5573 if (typ == NULL((void*)0)) return 0;
5574
5575 if (typ->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
5576 return 1;
5577 }
5578
5579 if (typ->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
5580 sm_ref ctype =
5581 typ->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
5582 if (ctype == NULL((void*)0)) return 0;
5583 if (ctype->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
5584 return 1;
5585 }
5586 }
5587 return 0;
5588}
5589
5590static sm_ref
5591get_containing_structure(sm_ref expr)
5592{
5593 switch(expr->node_type) {
5594 case cod_element_ref:
5595 return get_containing_structure(expr->node.element_ref.array_ref);
5596 case cod_field_ref:
5597 return expr->node.field_ref.struct_ref;
5598 default:
5599 return NULL((void*)0);
5600 }
5601}
5602
5603
5604static void
5605add_field_list(int *format_count_p, FMStructDescList *format_list_p, sm_ref typ)
5606{
5607 sm_list fields = typ->node.struct_type_decl.fields;
5608 FMFieldList field_list = malloc(sizeof(field_list[0]) * 2);
5609 int field_count = 0;
5610 int my_format_num = (*format_count_p)++;
5611 *format_list_p = realloc(*format_list_p, sizeof(*format_list_p[0]) * (*format_count_p + 1));
5612 while(fields != NULL((void*)0)) {
5613 sm_ref typ = fields->node->node.field.sm_complex_type;
5614 field_list = realloc(field_list, (sizeof(field_list[0]) * (field_count +2)));
5615 field_list[field_count].field_name = strdup(fields->node->node.field.name);
5616 field_list[field_count].field_type = strdup(fields->node->node.field.string_type);
5617 field_list[field_count].field_size = fields->node->node.field.cg_size;
5618 field_list[field_count].field_offset = fields->node->node.field.cg_offset;
5619 while((typ != NULL((void*)0)) && ((typ->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) || (typ->node_type == cod_declaration)
5620 || (typ->node_type == cod_array_type_decl))) {
5621 if (typ->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
5622 typ = typ->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
5623 } else if (typ->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
5624 typ = typ->node.array_type_decl.sm_complex_element_type;
5625 } else if (typ->node_type == cod_declaration) {
5626 typ = typ->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
5627 }
5628 }
5629 if ((typ != NULL((void*)0)) && (typ->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl)) {
5630 add_field_list(format_count_p, format_list_p, typ);
5631 }
5632 field_count++;
5633 fields = fields->next;
5634 }
5635 field_list[field_count].field_name = field_list[field_count].field_type = NULL((void*)0);
5636 field_list[field_count].field_size = field_list[field_count].field_offset = 0;
5637 (*format_list_p)[my_format_num].format_name = strdup(typ->node.struct_type_decl.id);
5638 (*format_list_p)[my_format_num].field_list = field_list;
5639 (*format_list_p)[my_format_num].struct_size = typ->node.struct_type_decl.cg_size;
5640 (*format_list_p)[my_format_num].opt_info = NULL((void*)0);
5641}
5642
5643static FMStructDescList
5644build_format_list(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref expr)
5645{
5646 sm_ref typ = get_complex_type(context, expr);
5647 FMStructDescList formats = malloc(sizeof(formats[0]) * 2);
5648 int format_count = 0;
5649 if (typ == NULL((void*)0)) {
5650 cod_src_error(context, expr->node.field_ref.struct_ref,
5651 "Reference must be structured type",
5652 expr->node.field_ref.lx_field);
5653 return 0;
5654 }
5655 if (typ->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
5656 typ = typ->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
5657 }
5658 if (typ->node_type == cod_declaration) {
5659 typ = typ->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
5660 }
5661 add_field_list(&format_count, &formats, typ);
5662 formats[format_count].format_name = NULL((void*)0);
5663 formats[format_count].field_list = NULL((void*)0);
5664 return formats;
5665}
5666
5667static int is_left_hand_side(sm_ref expr);
5668
5669static int semanticize_expr(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref expr,
5670 scope_ptr scope)
5671{
5672 switch(expr->node_type) {
5673 case cod_identifier: {
5674 sm_ref tmp = resolve(expr->node.identifier.id, scope);
5675 if (tmp != NULL((void*)0)) {
5676 if (tmp->node_type == cod_constant) {
5677 srcpos old_srcpos = expr->node.identifier.lx_srcpos;
5678 free(expr->node.identifier.id);
5679 /* morph identifier into constant */
5680 expr->node_type = cod_constant;
5681 expr->node.constant.token = tmp->node.constant.token;
5682 expr->node.constant.const_val = strdup(tmp->node.constant.const_val);
5683 expr->node.constant.freeable_name = NULL((void*)0);
5684 expr->node.constant.lx_srcpos = old_srcpos;
5685 return semanticize_expr(context, expr, scope);
5686 } else {
5687 expr->node.identifier.sm_declaration = tmp;
5688 return 1;
5689 }
5690 } else {
5691 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5692 "Undefined Symbol \"%s\"",
5693 expr->node.identifier.id);
5694 return 0;
5695 }
5696 }
5697 case cod_comma_expression:
5698 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.comma_expression.left, scope))
5699 return 0;
5700 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.comma_expression.right, scope))
5701 return 0;
5702 return 1;
5703 case cod_cast: {
5704 int cg_type;
5705 sm_ref typ;
5706 if (expr->node.cast.expression &&
5707 !semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.cast.expression, scope)) {
5708 return 0;
5709 }
5710
5711 typ = reduce_type_list(context, expr->node.cast.type_spec, &cg_type,
5712 scope, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
5713 if ((cg_type == DILL_ERR) && (typ == NULL((void*)0))) {
5714 cod_src_error(context, expr, "Illegal cast");
5715 return 0;
5716 }
5717 expr->node.cast.cg_type = cg_type;
5718 expr->node.cast.sm_complex_type = typ;
5719 return 1;
5720 }
5721 case cod_operator: {
5722 int ret = 1;
5723 if (expr->node.operator.left != NULL((void*)0)) {
5724 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.operator.left, scope)) {
5725 ret = 0;
5726 }
5727 }
5728 if (expr->node.operator.right != NULL((void*)0)) {
5729 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.operator.right, scope)) {
5730 ret = 0;
5731 }
5732 }
5733 if (ret == 0) return 0;
5734 if ((expr->node.operator.left != NULL((void*)0)) &&
5735 (expr->node.operator.right != NULL((void*)0))) {
5736 expr->node.operator.operation_type =
5737 determine_op_type(context, expr,
5738 expr->node.operator.left,
5739 expr->node.operator.right);
5740 if (expr->node.operator.operation_type == DILL_ERR) {
5741 return 0;
5742 }
5743 } else if (expr->node.operator.right != NULL((void*)0)) {
5744 expr->node.operator.operation_type =
5745 determine_unary_type(context, expr, expr->node.operator.right);
5746 } else if (expr->node.operator.left != NULL((void*)0)) {
5747 expr->node.operator.operation_type =
5748 determine_unary_type(context, expr, expr->node.operator.left);
5749 }
5750 switch (expr->node.operator.op) {
5751 case op_leq: case op_lt: case op_geq: case op_gt: case op_neq:
5752 case op_eq: case op_log_neg: case op_log_or: case op_log_and:
5753 case op_sizeof:
5754 expr->node.operator.result_type = DILL_I;
5755 break;
5756 case op_address:
5757 expr->node.operator.result_type = DILL_P;
5758 if (expr->node.operator.right->node_type == cod_identifier) {
5759 sm_ref decl = expr->node.operator.right->node.identifier.sm_declaration;
5760 if (decl->node_type == cod_declaration) {
5761 if (decl->node.declaration.param_num != -1) {
5762 if (decl->node.declaration.sm_complex_type == NULL((void*)0)) {
5763 cod_src_error(context, expr, "Cannot take address of a pass-by-value parameter");
5764 return 0;
5765 }
5766 }
5767 decl->node.declaration.addr_taken = 1;
5768 }
5769 } else {
5770 if (!is_left_hand_side(expr->node.operator.right)) {
5771 cod_src_error(context, expr, "Invalid operand to address operator");
5772 return 0;
5773 }
5774 }
5775 break;
5776 case op_deref: {
5777 sm_ref typ = get_complex_type(context, expr->node.operator.right);
5778 if (!typ || ((typ->node_type != cod_reference_type_decl) &&
5779 (typ->node_type != cod_array_type_decl))) {
5780 cod_src_error(context, expr, "Cannot dereference a non-reference type");
5781 return 0;
5782 } else if (typ->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
5783 expr->node.operator.result_type =
5784 typ->node.reference_type_decl.cg_referenced_type;
5785 } else if (typ->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
5786 expr->node.operator.result_type =
5787 typ->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_type;
5788 } else {
5789 assert(0)((void) sizeof ((0) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (0) ; else __assert_fail
("0", "cod/cod.y", 3524, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__);
}));
5790 }
5791 break;
5792 }
5793 default:
5794 /* Operator applied to pointer types? Check compatibility... */
5795 if(expr->node.operator.operation_type == DILL_P) {
5796
5797 switch(expr->node.operator.op) {
5798 case op_inc:
5799 case op_dec:
5800 break;
5801
5802 case op_plus:
5803 {
5804 sm_ref left = expr->node.operator.left;
5805 sm_ref right = expr->node.operator.right;
5806
5807 sm_ref lcplx = NULL((void*)0);
5808 sm_ref rcplx = NULL((void*)0);
5809
5810 if(!left) {
5811 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5812 "Invalid operand to unary plus\n");
5813 return 0;
5814 }
5815
5816 /* Extract complex types, if any */
5817 lcplx = get_complex_type(context, left);
5818 rcplx = get_complex_type(context, right);
5819
5820 /* Pointers do not add with complex types */
5821 if(lcplx && rcplx) {
5822 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5823 "Invalid operands to binary plus");
5824 return 0;
5825 }
5826
5827 /*
5828 * We're ok if we reach this, since that implies we have subtraction
5829 * between a pointer and an integral type. The suitability of the
5830 * integral type has been checked in determine_op_type() already.
5831 */
5832 }
5833 break;
5834
5835 case op_minus:
5836 {
5837 sm_ref left = expr->node.operator.left;
5838 sm_ref right = expr->node.operator.right;
5839
5840 sm_ref lcplx = NULL((void*)0);
5841 sm_ref rcplx = NULL((void*)0);
5842
5843 if(!left) {
5844 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5845 "Invalid operand to unary minus\n");
5846 return 0;
5847 }
5848
5849 /* Extract complex types, if any */
5850 lcplx = get_complex_type(context, left);
5851 rcplx = get_complex_type(context, right);
5852
5853
5854 /* If both are complex types... */
5855 if(lcplx && rcplx) {
5856
5857 /* If both are pointers... */
5858 if(((lcplx->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) || (lcplx->node_type == cod_array_type_decl)) &&
5859 ((rcplx->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) || (rcplx->node_type == cod_array_type_decl))) {
5860 /* Check if the argument pointers are compatible */
5861 if(!are_compatible_ptrs(lcplx, rcplx)) {
5862 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5863 "Incompatible pointer arguments to binary minus");
5864 return 0;
5865 } else {
5866 /*
5867 * Binary minus between two compatible pointers is allowed,
5868 * but it produces an integral type, so we fix that here.
5869 */
5870 expr->node.operator.result_type=DILL_L;
5871
5872 /*
5873 * NOTE how we return success directly from here and do not
5874 * break from the switch through the line below setting the
5875 * result_type from the operation_type... In this case this
5876 * would cause problems. We want operation_type to stay DILL_P
5877 * but the final result_type to be a DILL_L.
5878 */
5879 return 1;
5880 }
5881 } else {
5882 /*
5883 * Pointers and other complex types do not subtract.
5884 * Arithmetic canno be done on non-pointer complex types.
5885 */
5886 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5887 "Incompatible arguments to binary minus");
5888 return 0;
5889 }
5890 }
5891
5892 /*
5893 * We're ok if we reach this, since that implies we have subtraction
5894 * between a pointer and an integral type. The suitability of the
5895 * integral type has been checked in determine_op_type() already.
5896 */
5897 }
5898 break;
5899
5900 default:
5901 cod_src_error(context, expr,
5902 "Operator cannot be applied to pointer types!\n");
5903 return 0;
5904 }
5905 }
5906 /*
5907 * NOTE: If anything here changes, one (potentially) has to
5908 * update the code above which deals with binary minus
5909 * between two compatible pointers, changes the result to
5910 * an integral type, and returns directly without going
5911 * through this code (as all other cases do).
5912 */
5913 expr->node.operator.result_type=expr->node.operator.operation_type;
5914 }
5915 return ret;
5916 }
5917 case cod_constant:
5918 return 1;
5919 case cod_assignment_expression: {
5920 int ret = 1;
5921 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.assignment_expression.left, scope)) {
5922 ret = 0;
5923 } else {
5924 expr->node.assignment_expression.cg_type =
5925 cod_sm_get_type(expr->node.assignment_expression.left);
5926 }
5927 if (expr->node.assignment_expression.left && is_const(expr->node.assignment_expression.left)) {
5928 cod_src_error(context, expr->node.assignment_expression.left, "Invalid assignment, left side is const");
5929 ret = 0;
5930 }
5931 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.assignment_expression.right, scope)){
5932 ret = 0;
5933 } else {
5934 int right_type =
5935 cod_sm_get_type(expr->node.assignment_expression.right);
5936 if ((right_type == DILL_P) &&
5937 (is_string(expr->node.assignment_expression.right))) {
5938 if (expr->node.assignment_expression.cg_type != DILL_P) {
5939 cod_src_error(context, expr, "assignment mixes string and non-string types");
5940 ret = 0;
5941 }
5942 } else if ((right_type == DILL_B) || (right_type == DILL_ERR)) {
5943 cod_src_error(context, expr->node.assignment_expression.right, "Invalid assignment, right side must be simple type");
5944 ret = 0;
5945 }
5946 }
5947 if ((expr->node.assignment_expression.cg_type == DILL_P) ||
5948 (expr->node.assignment_expression.cg_type == DILL_ERR)) {
5949 sm_ref ltyp =
5950 get_complex_type(context,
5951 expr->node.assignment_expression.left);
5952 sm_ref rtyp =
5953 get_complex_type(context,
5954 expr->node.assignment_expression.right);
5955 if (ltyp == NULL((void*)0)) {
5956 if (!is_string(expr->node.assignment_expression.left)) {
5957 cod_src_error(context, expr->node.assignment_expression.left, "Invalid assignment, left side must be simple, non-pointer type");
5958 ret = 0;
5959 }
5960 } else {
5961 if ((ltyp->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl) || (ltyp->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) || (ltyp->node_type == cod_enum_type_decl)) {
5962 /* maybe OK */
5963 } else if (ltyp->node_type != cod_reference_type_decl) {
5964 cod_src_error(context, expr->node.assignment_expression.left, "Invalid assignment, left side must be simple, non-pointer type");
5965 ret = 0;
5966 }
5967 }
5968 }
5969 if (ret == 1) {
5970 ret = assignment_types_match(context,
5971 expr->node.assignment_expression.left,
5972 expr->node.assignment_expression.right,
5973 /* strict */ (expr->node.assignment_expression.op == op_eq));
5974 }
5975 return ret;
5976 }
5977 case cod_field_ref: {
5978 sm_ref typ;
5979 sm_list fields;
5980 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.field_ref.struct_ref, scope)) {
5981 return 0;
5982 }
5983 typ = get_complex_type(context, expr->node.field_ref.struct_ref);
5984 if (typ == NULL((void*)0)) {
5985 cod_src_error(context, expr->node.field_ref.struct_ref,
5986 "Reference must be structured type",
5987 expr->node.field_ref.lx_field);
5988 return 0;
5989 }
5990 if (typ->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
5991 typ = typ->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
5992 }
5993 if (typ->node_type == cod_declaration) {
5994 typ = typ->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
5995 }
5996 fields = typ->node.struct_type_decl.fields;
5997 while(fields != NULL((void*)0)) {
5998 if (strcmp(expr->node.field_ref.lx_field,
5999 fields->node->node.field.name) == 0) {
6000 break;
6001 }
6002 fields = fields->next;
6003 }
6004 if (fields == NULL((void*)0)) {
6005 cod_src_error(context, expr,
6006 "Unknown field reference, \"%s\".",
6007 expr->node.field_ref.lx_field);
6008 return 0;
6009 }
6010 expr->node.field_ref.sm_field_ref = fields->node;
6011 return 1;
6012 }
6013 case cod_element_ref: {
6014 if (semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.element_ref.array_ref, scope)) {
6015 int cg_type;
6016 sm_ref arr = get_complex_type(NULL((void*)0), expr->node.element_ref.array_ref);
6017 if (is_string(expr->node.element_ref.array_ref)) {
6018 expr->node.element_ref.this_index_dimension = 0;
6019 expr->node.element_ref.sm_complex_element_type = NULL((void*)0);
6020 expr->node.element_ref.cg_element_type = DILL_C;
6021 expr->node.element_ref.sm_containing_structure_ref =
6022 get_containing_structure(expr->node.element_ref.array_ref);
6023 } else if (is_array(expr->node.element_ref.array_ref)) {
6024 if (arr->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
6025 arr = arr->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
6026 }
6027 if (expr->node.element_ref.array_ref->node_type != cod_element_ref) {
6028 /* bottom level of recursion, we're the left-most array index */
6029 expr->node.element_ref.this_index_dimension = 0;
6030 } else {
6031 sm_ref subindex = expr->node.element_ref.array_ref;
6032 expr->node.element_ref.this_index_dimension = subindex->node.element_ref.this_index_dimension + 1;
6033 }
6034 expr->node.element_ref.sm_complex_element_type =
6035 arr->node.array_type_decl.sm_complex_element_type;
6036
6037 expr->node.element_ref.cg_element_type =
6038 arr->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_type;
6039 expr->node.element_ref.sm_containing_structure_ref =
6040 get_containing_structure(expr->node.element_ref.array_ref);
6041 } else if (arr && (arr->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl)) {
6042 expr->node.element_ref.sm_complex_element_type =
6043 arr->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
6044 expr->node.element_ref.cg_element_type =
6045 arr->node.reference_type_decl.cg_referenced_type;
6046 expr->node.element_ref.sm_containing_structure_ref =
6047 get_containing_structure(expr->node.element_ref.array_ref);
6048 } else {
6049 cod_src_error(context, expr, "Indexed element must be array, string or reference type.");
6050 return 0;
6051 }
6052
6053 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.element_ref.expression, scope)) {
6054 return 0;
6055 }
6056
6057 cg_type = cod_sm_get_type(expr->node.element_ref.expression);
6058 switch(cg_type) {
6059 case DILL_C:
6060 case DILL_UC:
6061 case DILL_S:
6062 case DILL_US:
6063 case DILL_I:
6064 case DILL_U:
6065 case DILL_L:
6066 case DILL_UL:
6067 return 1;
6068 break;
6069 }
6070 cod_src_error(context, expr,
6071 "Index for element reference must be integer type");
6072 return 0;
6073 }
6074 return 0;
6075 }
6076 case cod_subroutine_call: {
6077 sm_ref func_ref = expr->node.subroutine_call.sm_func_ref;
6078 char *id;
6079 sm_ref tmp;
6080 sm_list args;
6081 sm_list formals, tmp_formals, tmp_args;
6082 int ret = 1;
6083 if (func_ref->node_type == cod_identifier) {
6084 id = func_ref->node.identifier.id;
6085 } else {
6086 id = func_ref->node.declaration.id;
6087 }
6088 tmp = resolve(id, scope);
6089 args = expr->node.subroutine_call.arguments;
6090 int done;
6091 if (tmp != NULL((void*)0)) {
6092 if ((tmp->node_type != cod_declaration) ||
6093 !tmp->node.declaration.is_subroutine) {
6094 cod_src_error(context, expr,
6095 "Identifier is not subroutine \"%s\".",
6096 func_ref->node.identifier.id);
6097 return 0;
6098 }
6099 free(func_ref->node.identifier.id);
6100 free(func_ref);
6101 expr->node.subroutine_call.sm_func_ref = func_ref = tmp;
6102 formals = func_ref->node.declaration.params;
6103 } else {
6104 cod_src_error(context, func_ref, "Undefined Subroutine \"%s\".",
6105 func_ref->node.identifier.id);
6106
6107 return 0;
6108 }
6109 tmp_formals = formals;
6110 tmp_args = args;
6111 sm_list *last_arg_p = &args;
6112 /* add closure args if required */
6113 while (tmp_formals != NULL((void*)0)) {
6114 sm_ref formal = tmp_formals->node;
6115 if (formal && (formal->node.declaration.sm_complex_type != NULL((void*)0))) {
6116 sm_ref ct = formal->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
6117 if ((ct->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) &&
6118 (strcmp(ct->node.reference_type_decl.name, "cod_closure_context") == 0)) {
6119 sm_list new_arg = malloc(sizeof(struct list_struct));
6120 char tmp[30];
6121 new_arg->next = tmp_args;
6122 if (func_ref->node.declaration.closure_id == NULL((void*)0)) {
6123 strcpy(tmp, "0");
6124 } else {
6125 sprintf(tmp, "%p", func_ref->node.declaration.closure_id);
6126 if (strncmp(tmp, "0x", 2) != 0) {
6127 sprintf(tmp, "0x%p", func_ref->node.declaration.closure_id);
6128 }
6129 }
6130
6131 new_arg->node = cod_new_constant();
6132 new_arg->node->node.constant.token = integer_constant;
6133 new_arg->node->node.constant.const_val = strdup(tmp);
6134 *last_arg_p = new_arg;
6135 tmp_args = new_arg;
6136 } else if ((ct->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) &&
6137 (strcmp(ct->node.reference_type_decl.name, "cod_exec_context") == 0)) {
6138 tmp_formals = tmp_formals->next;
6139 continue;
6140 }
6141
6142 }
6143 tmp_formals = tmp_formals->next;
6144 if (tmp_args) {
6145 last_arg_p = &tmp_args->next;
6146 tmp_args = tmp_args->next;
6147 }
6148 }
6149 /* must do this assigment, in case things changed from the loop above */
6150 expr->node.subroutine_call.arguments = args;
6151
6152 done = 0;
6153 while (!done) {
6154 sm_ref arg = NULL((void*)0);
6155 sm_ref formal = NULL((void*)0);
6156 if (formals != NULL((void*)0)) {
6157 formal = formals->node;
6158 }
6159 if (args != NULL((void*)0)) {
6160 arg = args->node;
6161 }
6162 if (formal && (formal->node.declaration.sm_complex_type != NULL((void*)0))) {
6163 sm_ref ct = formal->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
6164 if ((ct->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) &&
6165 (ct->node.reference_type_decl.name != NULL((void*)0))) {
6166 if (strcmp(ct->node.reference_type_decl.name, "cod_exec_context") == 0) {
6167 if (context->has_exec_context == 0) {
6168 cod_src_error(context, arg, "Calling subroutine has no cod_exec_context");
6169 return 0;
6170 }
6171 /* swallow next formal, we'll fill that in ourselves */
6172 formals = formals->next;
6173 continue;
6174 }
6175 }
6176 }
6177 if ((args == NULL((void*)0)) && (formals != NULL((void*)0))) {
6178 if (strcmp(formal->node.declaration.id, "...") != 0) {
6179 cod_src_error(context, arg, "Too few arguments to function");
6180 ret = 0;
6181 }
6182 }
6183 if (args == NULL((void*)0)) {
6184 done++;
6185 continue;
6186 }
6187 if (!semanticize_expr(context, arg, scope) ) {
6188 args = args->next;
6189 continue;
6190 }
6191 if (formal == NULL((void*)0)) {
6192 cod_src_error(context, arg, "Too many arguments to subroutine");
6193 ret = 0;
6194 return ret;
6195 }
6196 if (strcmp(formal->node.declaration.id, "...") != 0) {
6197 /* we've got a real formal to check against */
6198 /* do some checking... */
6199 int mismatch = 0;
6200 switch (cod_sm_get_type(arg)) {
6201 case DILL_D: case DILL_F:
6202 if (formal->node.declaration.cg_type >= DILL_V) {
6203 mismatch++;
6204 }
6205 break;
6206 case DILL_I: case DILL_U:
6207 case DILL_L: case DILL_UL:
6208 if (formal->node.declaration.cg_type == DILL_P) {
6209 sm_ref ct = formal->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
6210 if (!ct ||
6211 (ct->node_type != cod_reference_type_decl) ||
6212 ((strcmp(ct->node.reference_type_decl.name, "cod_type_spec") != 0) &&
6213 (strcmp(ct->node.reference_type_decl.name, "cod_closure_context") != 0))) {
6214 if ((arg->node_type != cod_constant) ||
6215 (arg->node.constant.token != integer_constant)) {
6216 mismatch++;
6217 } else {
6218 int tmp = -1;
6219 sscanf(arg->node.constant.const_val, "%d", &tmp);
6220 /* zero is an acceptable pointer */
6221 if (tmp != 0) {
6222 mismatch++;
6223 }
6224 }
6225 }
6226 }
6227 break;
6228 case DILL_P:
6229 if (formal->node.declaration.cg_type != DILL_P) {
6230 if (!(formal->node.declaration.sm_complex_type &&
6231 (formal->node.declaration.sm_complex_type->node_type ==
6232 cod_reference_type_decl))) {
6233 mismatch++;
6234 }
6235 }
6236 break;
6237 }
6238
6239 if (mismatch) {
6240 cod_src_error(context, arg,
6241 "Type mismatch, parameter \"%s\".",
6242 formal->node.declaration.id);
6243 ret = 0;
6244 }
6245 }
6246 if ((formals != NULL((void*)0)) &&
6247 (strcmp(formal->node.declaration.id, "...") != 0)) {
6248 formals = formals->next;
6249 formal = NULL((void*)0);
6250 if (formals != NULL((void*)0)) formal = formals->node;
6251 }
6252 /* look ahead to next formal and insert an arg if it's cod_type_spec */
6253 if (formal &&
6254 formal->node.declaration.sm_complex_type != NULL((void*)0)) {
6255 sm_ref ct = formal->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
6256 if ((ct->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) &&
6257 (strcmp(ct->node.reference_type_decl.name, "cod_type_spec")
6258 == 0)) {
6259 /* swallow next formal, we'll fill that in ourselves */
6260 sm_list tmp_args = malloc(sizeof(struct list_struct));
6261 FMStructDescList list = build_format_list(context, arg);
6262 char tmp[30];
6263 sprintf(&tmp[0], "0x%p", list);
6264 tmp_args->node = cod_new_constant();
6265 tmp_args->node->node.constant.token = integer_constant;
6266 tmp_args->node->node.constant.const_val = strdup(tmp);
6267 tmp_args->next = args->next;
6268 args->next = tmp_args;
6269 }
6270 }
6271 args = args->next;
6272 if ((args == NULL((void*)0)) && (formals != NULL((void*)0))) {
6273 if (strcmp(formal->node.declaration.id, "...") != 0) {
6274 cod_src_error(context, arg, "Too few arguments to function");
6275 ret = 0;
6276 }
6277 }
6278 }
6279 return ret;
6280 }
6281 case cod_conditional_operator: {
6282 int ret = 1;
6283 if (expr->node.conditional_operator.condition != NULL((void*)0)) {
6284 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.conditional_operator.condition, scope)) {
6285 ret = 0;
6286 }
6287 }
6288 if (expr->node.conditional_operator.e1 != NULL((void*)0)) {
6289 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.conditional_operator.e1, scope)) {
6290 ret = 0;
6291 }
6292 }
6293 if (expr->node.conditional_operator.e2 != NULL((void*)0)) {
6294 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.conditional_operator.e2, scope)) {
6295 ret = 0;
6296 }
6297 }
6298 expr->node.conditional_operator.result_type =
6299 determine_unary_type(context, expr, expr->node.conditional_operator.e1);
6300 return ret;
6301 }
6302 case cod_initializer_list: {
6303 sm_list items = expr->node.initializer_list.initializers;
6304 int ret = 1;
6305 while (items) {
6306 if (!semanticize_expr(context, items->node, scope)) ret = 0;
6307 items = items->next;
6308 }
6309 return ret;
6310 }
6311 case cod_initializer: {
6312 if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.initializer.initializer, scope))
6313 return 0;
6314 if (expr->node.initializer.designation) {
6315// if (!semanticize_expr(context, expr->node.initializer.designation, scope)) return 0;
6316 }
6317 return 1;
6318 }
6319 default:
6320 fprintf(stderrstderr, "Unknown case in semanticize_expression\n");
6321 cod_print(expr);
6322 }
6323 return 0;
6324}
6325
6326static int
6327is_left_hand_side(sm_ref expr)
6328{
6329 switch(expr->node_type) {
6330 case cod_identifier:
6331 return 1;
6332 case cod_operator:
6333 return 0;
6334 case cod_cast:
6335 return is_left_hand_side(expr->node.cast.expression);
6336 case cod_assignment_expression:
6337 return expr->node.assignment_expression.cg_type;
6338 case cod_declaration:
6339 return 1;
6340 case cod_constant:
6341 return 0;
6342 case cod_field_ref:
6343 return 1;
6344 case cod_element_ref:
6345 return 1;
6346 case cod_subroutine_call:
6347 return 0;
6348 default:
6349 fprintf(stderrstderr, "Unknown case in is_left_hand_side()\n");
6350 cod_print(expr);
6351 assert(0)((void) sizeof ((0) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (0) ; else __assert_fail
("0", "cod/cod.y", 4086, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__);
}));
6352 }
6353 return 0;
6354}
6355
6356int
6357type_of_int_const_string(char *val)
6358{
6359/*
6360For decimal, it is the first type the value can fit in: int, long, long long
6361
6362For hexadecimal, it is the first type the value can fit in: int, unsigned int, long,
6363unsigned long, long long, unsigned long long
6364*/
6365
6366 int ret = DILL_I;
6367 long i;
6368 int len = strlen(val);
6369 int hex = 0;
6370 int specified_unsgned = 0, specified_lng = 0;
6371 if (val[0] == '0') {
6372 /* hex or octal */
6373 hex++;
6374 if (val[1] == 'x') {
6375 /* hex */
6376 if (sscanf(val+2, "%lx", &i) != 1)
6377 printf("hex sscanf failed, %s\n", val);
6378 } else if (val[1] == 'b') {
6379 /* binary */
6380 int j = 2;
6381 i = 0;
6382 while (val[j]) {
6383 i <<= 1;
6384 if (val[j] == '1') {
6385 i += 1;
6386 }
6387 j++;
6388 }
6389 } else {
6390 if (sscanf(val, "%lo", &i) != 1)
6391 printf("octal sscanf failed %s\n", val);
6392 }
6393 } else {
6394 if (sscanf(val, "%ld", &i) != 1)
6395 printf("decimal sscanf failed %s\n", val);
6396 }
6397 switch(val[len-1]) {
6398 case 'U':
6399 case 'u':
6400 specified_unsgned++;
6401 break;
6402 case 'l':
6403 case 'L':
6404 specified_lng++;
6405 break;
6406 }
6407 if (len > 2)
6408 switch(val[len-2]) {
6409 case 'U':
6410 case 'u':
6411 specified_unsgned++;
6412 break;
6413 case 'l':
6414 case 'L':
6415 specified_lng++;
6416 break;
6417 }
6418 if (len > 3)
6419 switch(val[len-3]) {
6420 case 'U':
6421 case 'u':
6422 specified_unsgned++;
6423 break;
6424 case 'l':
6425 case 'L':
6426 specified_lng++;
6427 break;
6428 }
6429 if (specified_lng == 0) {
6430 /* unspecified */
6431 if (hex) {
6432 if (i == (int)i) return DILL_I;
6433 if (i == (unsigned)i) return DILL_U;
6434 if (i == (long)i) return DILL_L;
6435 if (i == (unsigned)i) return DILL_UL;
6436 return DILL_UL; /* don't do long long now */
6437 } else {
6438 if (i == (int)i) return DILL_I;
6439 if (i == (long)i) return DILL_L;
6440 return DILL_L; /* don't do long long now */
6441 }
6442 }
6443 /* must have specified long */
6444 if (specified_unsgned) {
6445 return DILL_UL;
6446 } else {
6447 return DILL_L;
6448 }
6449}
6450
6451extern int
6452cod_sm_get_type(sm_ref node)
6453{
6454 switch(node->node_type) {
6455 case cod_identifier:
6456 if (node->node.identifier.sm_declaration != NULL((void*)0)) {
6457 return cod_sm_get_type(node->node.identifier.sm_declaration);
6458 }
6459 return node->node.identifier.cg_type;
6460 case cod_enumerator:
6461 return DILL_I;
6462 case cod_operator:
6463 return node->node.operator.result_type;
6464 case cod_conditional_operator:
6465 return node->node.conditional_operator.result_type;
6466 case cod_cast:
6467 return node->node.cast.cg_type;
6468 case cod_assignment_expression:
6469 return node->node.assignment_expression.cg_type;
6470 case cod_declaration:
6471 if (is_array(node)) {
6472 return DILL_P;
6473 } else {
6474 return node->node.declaration.cg_type;
6475 }
6476 case cod_constant:
6477 /* need to handle bigger constants */
6478 if (node->node.constant.token == string_constant) {
6479 return DILL_P;
6480 } else if (node->node.constant.token == floating_constant) {
6481 return DILL_D;
6482 } else if (node->node.constant.token == character_constant) {
6483 return DILL_C;
6484 } else {
6485 return type_of_int_const_string(node->node.constant.const_val);
6486 }
6487 case cod_field_ref:
6488 return cod_sm_get_type(node->node.field_ref.sm_field_ref);
6489 case cod_element_ref:
6490 return node->node.element_ref.cg_element_type;
6491 case cod_field:
6492 if (is_array(node)) {
6493 return DILL_P;
6494 } else {
6495 return node->node.field.cg_type;
6496 }
6497 case cod_initializer_list:
6498 return DILL_ERR;
6499 case cod_subroutine_call:
6500 return cod_sm_get_type(node->node.subroutine_call.sm_func_ref);
6501 case cod_comma_expression:
6502 return cod_sm_get_type(node->node.comma_expression.right);
6503 default:
6504 fprintf(stderrstderr, "Unknown case in cod_sm_get_type()\n");
6505 cod_print(node);
6506 }
6507 return DILL_ERR;
6508}
6509
6510extern int
6511are_compatible_ptrs(sm_ref left, sm_ref right) {
6512 sm_ref lTyp = NULL((void*)0), rTyp = NULL((void*)0);
6513 int lcgTyp = -1, rcgTyp = -1;
6514
6515 /* Sanity check */
6516 if (left->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
6517 lTyp = left->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
6518 lcgTyp = left->node.reference_type_decl.cg_referenced_type;
6519 } else if (left->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
6520 lTyp = left->node.array_type_decl.sm_complex_element_type;
6521 lcgTyp = left->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_type;
6522 } else {
6523 return 0;
6524 }
6525 if (right->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
6526 rTyp = right->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
6527 rcgTyp = right->node.reference_type_decl.cg_referenced_type;
6528 } else if (right->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
6529 rTyp = right->node.array_type_decl.sm_complex_element_type;
6530 rcgTyp = right->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_type;
6531 } else {
6532 return 0;
6533 }
6534
6535 if(lTyp && rTyp) {
6536 /* Two complex referenced types */
6537 if(((lTyp->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) || (lTyp->node_type == cod_array_type_decl)) &&
6538 ((rTyp->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) || (rTyp->node_type == cod_array_type_decl))) {
6539 /* Recurse if both are pointers */
6540 return are_compatible_ptrs(lTyp, rTyp);
6541 }
6542 return (lTyp == rTyp)?1:0;
6543 }
6544
6545 if(!lTyp && !rTyp) {
6546 /* Two integral referenced types */
6547 return (rcgTyp == lcgTyp)?1:0;
6548 }
6549
6550 /* Mix of a pointer to a complex type and a pointer to an integral type */
6551 return 0;
6552}
6553
6554extern sm_ref
6555get_complex_type(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref node)
6556{
6557 if (!node) return NULL((void*)0);
6558 switch(node->node_type) {
6559 case cod_array_type_decl:
6560 case cod_reference_type_decl:
6561 case cod_struct_type_decl:
6562 case cod_enum_type_decl:
6563 return node;
6564 case cod_subroutine_call:
6565 return get_complex_type(context,
6566 node->node.subroutine_call.sm_func_ref);
6567 case cod_identifier:
6568 return get_complex_type(context,
6569 node->node.identifier.sm_declaration);
6570 case cod_element_ref:
6571 return node->node.element_ref.sm_complex_element_type;
6572 case cod_field:
6573 return node->node.field.sm_complex_type;
6574 case cod_declaration:
6575 return get_complex_type(context, node->node.declaration.sm_complex_type);
6576 case cod_field_ref:{
6577 sm_ref typ;
6578 sm_list fields;
6579 typ = get_complex_type(context, node->node.field_ref.struct_ref);
6580 if (typ->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
6581 typ = typ->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
6582 }
6583 if (typ->node_type == cod_declaration) {
6584 typ = typ->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
6585 }
6586 fields = typ->node.struct_type_decl.fields;
6587 while ((fields != NULL((void*)0)) &&
6588 (strcmp(node->node.field_ref.lx_field,
6589 fields->node->node.field.name) != 0)) {
6590 fields = fields->next;
6591 }
6592 if (fields == NULL((void*)0)) {
6593 cod_src_error(context, node, "Unknown field reference \"%s\".",
6594 node->node.field_ref.lx_field);
6595 return NULL((void*)0);
6596 }
6597 return get_complex_type(context, fields->node->node.field.sm_complex_type);
6598 }
6599 case cod_conditional_operator:
6600 return NULL((void*)0);
6601 case cod_constant:
6602 return NULL((void*)0);
6603 case cod_operator:
6604 switch (node->node.operator.op) {
6605 case op_deref: {
6606 sm_ref right = get_complex_type(NULL((void*)0), node->node.operator.right);
6607 if ((right != NULL((void*)0)) &&
6608 (right->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl)) {
6609 sm_ref typ = right->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type;
6610 if (typ && (typ->node_type == cod_declaration)) {
6611 return get_complex_type(context, typ);
6612 } else {
6613 return typ;
6614 }
6615 }
6616 return NULL((void*)0);
6617 }
6618 case op_plus: case op_minus: case op_inc: case op_dec: {
6619 sm_ref right = NULL((void*)0);
6620 sm_ref left = NULL((void*)0);
6621 if (node->node.operator.right)
6622 right = get_complex_type(NULL((void*)0), node->node.operator.right);
6623 if (node->node.operator.left)
6624 left = get_complex_type(NULL((void*)0), node->node.operator.left);
6625 if (right && (left == NULL((void*)0))) return right;
6626 if (left && (right == NULL((void*)0))) return left;
6627 if ((left == NULL((void*)0)) && (right == NULL((void*)0))) return NULL((void*)0);
6628 /*
6629 * GANEV: op_minus can be applied to two pointers,
6630 * i.e. two complex types => both left _and_ right can be
6631 * non-NULL, hence this code. This shouldn't happen in
6632 * other cases... (I think).
6633 */
6634 if(node->node.operator.op == op_minus && right && left) {
6635 if(left->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl &&
6636 right->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
6637 /* Ok, so it's op_minus between two pointers, then check compatibility */
6638 if(are_compatible_ptrs(left, right)) {
6639 return left;
6640 } else {
6641 cod_src_error(context, node,
6642 "Incompatible pointer args to binary minus");
6643 return NULL((void*)0);
6644 }
6645 }
6646 }
6647 cod_src_error(context, node, "Incompatible pointer arguments to operator");
6648 return NULL((void*)0);
6649 }
6650 default:
6651 return NULL((void*)0);
6652 }
6653
6654 case cod_cast:
6655 return node->node.cast.sm_complex_type;
6656 break;
6657 case cod_initializer_list:
6658 case cod_enumerator:
6659 return NULL((void*)0);
6660 case cod_assignment_expression:
6661 return get_complex_type(context, node->node.assignment_expression.left);
6662 default:
6663 fprintf(stderrstderr, "Unknown case in get_complex_type()\n");
6664 cod_print(node);
6665 }
6666 return NULL((void*)0);
6667}
6668
6669static sm_ref
6670reduce_type_list(cod_parse_context context, sm_list type_list, int *cg_type,
6671 scope_ptr scope, int*is_typedef, sm_ref *freeable_type)
6672{
6673 sm_list orig_list = type_list;
6674 int short_appeared = 0;
6675 int long_appeared = 0;
6676 int long_long_appeared = 0;
6677 int int_appeared = 0;
6678 int double_appeared = 0;
6679 int float_appeared = 0;
6680 int char_appeared = 0;
6681 int signed_appeared = 0;
6682 int unsigned_appeared = 0;
6683 int void_appeared = 0;
6684 int string_appeared = 0;
6685 int spec_count = 0;
6686 int prefix_end = 0;
6687 int type_found = 0;
6688 sm_ref complex_return_type = NULL((void*)0);;
6689
6690 *cg_type = DILL_ERR;
6691 while ((type_list != NULL((void*)0)) && (prefix_end == 0)) {
6692 int typ = type_list->node->node.type_specifier.token;
6693 if ((type_list->node->node_type != cod_type_specifier) ||
6694 (typ == STAR) || (typ == AT)) {
6695 prefix_end = 1;
6696 } else {
6697 spec_count++;
6698 switch (typ) {
6699 case INT:
6700 int_appeared++;
6701 break;
6702 case LONG:
6703 long_appeared++;
6704 break;
6705 case SHORT:
6706 short_appeared++;
6707 break;
6708 case DOUBLE:
6709 double_appeared++;
6710 break;
6711 case STRING:
6712 string_appeared++;
6713 break;
6714 case VOID:
6715 void_appeared++;
6716 break;
6717 case FLOAT:
6718 float_appeared++;
6719 break;
6720 case CHAR:
6721 char_appeared++;
6722 break;
6723 case SIGNED:
6724 signed_appeared++;
6725 break;
6726 case UNSIGNED:
6727 unsigned_appeared++;
6728 break;
6729 case TYPEDEF:
6730 if (is_typedef) (*is_typedef)++;
6731 spec_count--;
6732 break;
6733 case STATIC:
6734 spec_count--;
6735 break;
6736 case EXTERN_TOKEN:
6737 spec_count--;
6738 break;
6739 case CONST:
6740 spec_count--;
6741 break;
6742 default:
6743 printf("Unknown type\n");
6744 }
6745 type_list = type_list->next;
6746 }
6747 }
6748 if (spec_count == 0) {
6749 if (type_list == NULL((void*)0)) *cg_type = DILL_I; /* default to int */
6750 goto finalize;
6751 }
6752 if (void_appeared && (spec_count > 1)) {
6753 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node,
6754 "Void type may not appear with other specifiers");
6755 *cg_type = DILL_ERR;
6756 return NULL((void*)0);
6757 }
6758 if (string_appeared && (spec_count > 1)) {
6759 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node,
6760 "String type may not appear with other specifiers");
6761 *cg_type = DILL_ERR;
6762 return NULL((void*)0);
6763 }
6764 if (void_appeared) {
6765 *cg_type = DILL_V;
6766 goto finalize;
6767 }
6768 if (string_appeared) {
6769 *cg_type = DILL_P;
6770 goto finalize;
6771 }
6772 if (short_appeared && long_appeared ) {
6773 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node,
6774 "Only one of long or short permitted");
6775 *cg_type = DILL_ERR;
6776 return NULL((void*)0);
6777 }
6778 if (short_appeared && (double_appeared + float_appeared)) {
6779 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node,
6780 "Short may not be specified with double or float");
6781 *cg_type = DILL_ERR;
6782 return NULL((void*)0);
6783 }
6784 if (double_appeared + float_appeared) {
6785 if (double_appeared + float_appeared + short_appeared + signed_appeared + unsigned_appeared + char_appeared + int_appeared > 1) {
6786 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node, "Bad type spec");
6787 *cg_type = DILL_ERR;
6788 return NULL((void*)0);
6789 } else {
6790 /* not handling LONG plus one of these */
6791 if (double_appeared) {
6792 *cg_type = DILL_D;
6793 goto finalize;
6794 } else {
6795 *cg_type = DILL_F;
6796 goto finalize;
6797 }
6798 }
6799 }
6800
6801 /* neither float or double appeared */
6802 if (long_appeared == 2) {
6803 long_long_appeared++;
6804 long_appeared = 0;
6805 }
6806 if (short_appeared + char_appeared + long_appeared + long_long_appeared >= 2) {
6807 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node,
6808 "Only one integer size spec may be specified");
6809 *cg_type = DILL_ERR;
6810 return NULL((void*)0);
6811 }
6812 if (unsigned_appeared + signed_appeared > 1) {
6813 cod_src_error(context, orig_list->node, "Bad type spec");
6814 *cg_type = DILL_ERR;
6815 return NULL((void*)0);
6816 }
6817 if (unsigned_appeared) {
6818 if (char_appeared) {
6819 *cg_type = DILL_UC;
6820 goto finalize;
6821 } else if (short_appeared) {
6822 *cg_type = DILL_US;
6823 goto finalize;
6824 } else if (long_appeared || long_long_appeared) {
6825 *cg_type = DILL_UL;
6826 goto finalize;
6827 } else {
6828 *cg_type = DILL_U;
6829 goto finalize;
6830 }
6831 } else {
6832 if (char_appeared) {
6833 *cg_type = DILL_C;
6834 goto finalize;
6835 } else if (short_appeared) {
6836 *cg_type = DILL_S;
6837 goto finalize;
6838 } else if (long_appeared || long_long_appeared) {
6839 *cg_type = DILL_L;
6840 goto finalize;
6841 } else if (int_appeared) {
6842 *cg_type = DILL_I;
6843 goto finalize;
6844 }
6845 }
6846 finalize:
6847 if (type_list == NULL((void*)0)) {
6848 /* no error and no more to process */
6849 return NULL((void*)0);
6850 }
6851 if (*cg_type != DILL_ERR) {
6852 type_found++;
6853 }
6854 while (type_list != NULL((void*)0)) {
6855 sm_ref node = type_list->node;
6856 switch (node->node_type) {
6857 case cod_identifier:
6858 {
6859 if (type_found != 0) {
6860 cod_src_error(context, node,
6861 "Type identifier cannot follow prior identifiers");
6862 *cg_type = DILL_ERR;
6863 return NULL((void*)0);
6864 }
6865 complex_return_type = find_complex_type(node, scope);
6866 if ((complex_return_type != NULL((void*)0))&&
6867 (complex_return_type->node_type == cod_declaration)) {
6868 if (complex_return_type->node.declaration.sm_complex_type) {
6869 complex_return_type = complex_return_type->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
6870 } else {
6871 *cg_type = complex_return_type->node.declaration.cg_type;
6872 }
6873 }
6874 if ((complex_return_type != NULL((void*)0))&&
6875 (complex_return_type->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl)) {
6876 *cg_type = DILL_P;
6877 }
6878 if ((complex_return_type != NULL((void*)0))&&
6879 (complex_return_type->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl)) {
6880 *cg_type = DILL_B;
6881 }
6882 if ((complex_return_type != NULL((void*)0))&&
6883 (complex_return_type->node_type == cod_enum_type_decl)) {
6884 *cg_type = DILL_I;
6885 }
6886 if ((complex_return_type == NULL((void*)0)) && node->node.identifier.id &&
6887 ((strcmp(node->node.identifier.id, "cod_type_spec") == 0) ||
6888 (strcmp(node->node.identifier.id, "cod_closure_context") == 0) ||
6889 (strcmp(node->node.identifier.id, "cod_exec_context") == 0))) {
6890 /* special ECL type information for prior arg */
6891 sm_ref typ = cod_new_reference_type_decl();
6892 typ->node.reference_type_decl.name = strdup(node->node.identifier.id);
6893 if (strcmp(node->node.identifier.id, "cod_type_spec") == 0) {
6894 *cg_type = DILL_P;
6895 } else if (strcmp(node->node.identifier.id, "cod_closure_context") == 0) {
6896 *cg_type = DILL_P;
6897 } else {
6898 context->has_exec_context = 1;
6899 *cg_type = DILL_P;
6900 }
6901 typ->node.reference_type_decl.cg_referenced_type = *cg_type;
6902 typ->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type =
6903 complex_return_type;
6904 typ->node.reference_type_decl.kernel_ref = 0;
6905 complex_return_type = typ;
6906 if (*freeable_type) {
6907 cod_rfree(*freeable_type);
6908 *freeable_type = NULL((void*)0);
6909 }
6910 *freeable_type = typ;
6911 }
6912 assert((complex_return_type != NULL) || (*cg_type != DILL_ERR))((void) sizeof (((complex_return_type != ((void*)0)) || (*cg_type
!= DILL_ERR)) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if ((complex_return_type
!= ((void*)0)) || (*cg_type != DILL_ERR)) ; else __assert_fail
("(complex_return_type != NULL) || (*cg_type != DILL_ERR)", "cod/cod.y"
, 4647, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
6913 type_found++;
6914 }
6915 break;
6916 case cod_type_specifier:
6917 switch (node->node.type_specifier.token) {
6918 case STAR:
6919 {
6920 if (node->node.type_specifier.created_type_decl == NULL((void*)0)) {
6921 /* GSE create anon-type */
6922 sm_ref typ = cod_new_reference_type_decl();
6923 typ->node.reference_type_decl.name = gen_anon();
6924 typ->node.reference_type_decl.cg_referenced_type = *cg_type;
6925 *cg_type = DILL_P;
6926 typ->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type =
6927 complex_return_type;
6928 typ->node.reference_type_decl.kernel_ref = 0;
6929 complex_return_type = typ;
6930 node->node.type_specifier.created_type_decl = typ;
6931 } else {
6932 complex_return_type = node->node.type_specifier.created_type_decl;
6933 *cg_type = DILL_P;
6934 }
6935 }
6936 break;
6937 case AT:
6938 {
6939 /* GSE create anon-type */
6940 sm_ref typ = cod_new_reference_type_decl();
6941 typ->node.reference_type_decl.name = gen_anon();
6942 typ->node.reference_type_decl.cg_referenced_type = *cg_type;
6943 *cg_type = DILL_P;
6944 typ->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type =
6945 complex_return_type;
6946 typ->node.reference_type_decl.kernel_ref = 1;
6947 complex_return_type = typ;
6948 }
6949 break;
6950 default:
6951 if (type_found != 0) {
6952 cod_src_error(context, node,
6953 "Only '*', '@', and CONST can follow valid type");
6954 *cg_type = DILL_ERR;
6955 return NULL((void*)0);
6956 }
6957 }
6958 break;
6959 case cod_struct_type_decl: {
6960 if (node->node.struct_type_decl.fields != NULL((void*)0)) {
6961 semanticize_decl(context, node, scope);
6962 complex_return_type = node;
6963 } else {
6964 complex_return_type = resolve(node->node.struct_type_decl.id, scope);
6965 if (complex_return_type == NULL((void*)0)) {
6966 cod_src_error(context, node,
6967 "Struct declaration not found");
6968 return NULL((void*)0);
6969 }
6970 }
6971 *cg_type = DILL_B;
6972 break;
6973 }
6974 case cod_enum_type_decl: {
6975 if (node->node.enum_type_decl.enums != NULL((void*)0)) {
6976 semanticize_decl(context, node, scope);
6977 complex_return_type = node;
6978 } else {
6979 complex_return_type = resolve(node->node.enum_type_decl.id, scope);
6980 if (complex_return_type == NULL((void*)0)) {
6981 cod_src_error(context, node,
6982 "Enum declaration not found");
6983 return NULL((void*)0);
6984 }
6985 }
6986 *cg_type = DILL_I;
6987 break;
6988 }
6989 default:
6990 printf("Unexpected node in reduce_type_list\n");
6991 return NULL((void*)0);
6992 }
6993 type_list = type_list->next;
6994 }
6995 return complex_return_type;
6996}
6997
6998static int
6999assignment_types_match(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref left, sm_ref right, int strict)
7000{
7001 sm_ref left_smt, right_smt;
7002 int left_cgt, right_cgt;
7003 left_smt = get_complex_type(context, left);
7004 right_smt = get_complex_type(context, right);
7005 left_cgt = cod_sm_get_type(left);
7006 right_cgt = cod_sm_get_type(right);
7007 if ((left_smt == NULL((void*)0)) && (right_smt == NULL((void*)0))) {
7008 /* just check cgts */
7009 /* don't mix DILL_P, DILL_B and anything else */
7010 switch (left_cgt) {
7011 case DILL_P:
7012 switch (right_cgt) {
7013 case DILL_P:
7014 case DILL_L:
7015 case DILL_UL:
7016 return 1;
7017 break;
7018 default:
7019 cod_src_error(context, left, "Trying to assign a pointer variable with a non-pointer value.");
7020 return 0;
7021 }
7022 default:
7023 switch (right_cgt) {
7024 case DILL_P:
7025 cod_src_error(context, left, "Trying to assign pointer to an incompatible variable.");
7026 return 0;
7027 default:
7028 return 1;
7029 break;
7030 }
7031 }
7032 }
7033 if ((left_smt != NULL((void*)0)) &&
7034 ((left_smt->node_type != cod_reference_type_decl) &&
7035 (left_smt->node_type != cod_array_type_decl) &&
7036 (left_smt->node_type != cod_struct_type_decl) &&
7037 (left_smt->node_type != cod_enum_type_decl))) {
7038 if ((left_cgt == DILL_P) || (left_cgt == DILL_B)) {
7039 cod_src_error(context, left, "Only pointer, array, struct or enum complex types allowed as LHS in assignment");
7040 return 0;
7041 }
7042 }
7043 if ((right_smt != NULL((void*)0)) &&
7044 ((right_smt->node_type != cod_reference_type_decl) &&
7045 (right_smt->node_type != cod_array_type_decl) &&
7046 (right_smt->node_type != cod_struct_type_decl) &&
7047 (right_smt->node_type != cod_enum_type_decl))) {
7048 if ((right_cgt == DILL_P) || (right_cgt == DILL_B)) {
7049 cod_src_error(context, right, "Only pointer, array, struct or enum complex types allowed as RHS in assignment");
7050 return 0;
7051 }
7052 }
7053 if (left_smt && (left_smt->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) &&
7054 (right_smt == NULL((void*)0))) {
7055
7056 switch(right_cgt) {
7057 case DILL_P:
7058 case DILL_L:
7059 case DILL_UL:
