7060 return 1;
7061 case DILL_I:
7062 case DILL_U:
7063 if (!strict) return 1;
7064 if ((right->node_type == cod_constant) &&
7065 (right->node.constant.token == integer_constant)) {
7066 int i = -1;
7067 sscanf(right->node.constant.const_val, "%d", &i);
7068 if (i== 0) return 1;
7069 }
7070 /* falling through */
7071 default:
7072 cod_src_error(context, right, "Right hand side must be pointer type");
7073 return 0;
7074 }
7075 }
7076 if (right_smt && (left_smt == NULL((void*)0))) {
7077 switch(left_cgt) {
7078 case DILL_C:
7079 case DILL_UC:
7080 case DILL_S:
7081 case DILL_US:
7082 case DILL_I:
7083 case DILL_U:
7084 case DILL_L:
7085 case DILL_UL:
7086 case DILL_P:
7087 /* GANEV: should we have a warning here? */
7088 return 1;
7089
7090 default:
7091 cod_src_error(context, right, "Pointer converted without explicit cast");
7092 return 0;
7093 }
7094 }
7095 return 1;
7096}
7097
7098static int semanticize_struct_type_node(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref decl,
7099 scope_ptr scope);
7100
7101static int semanticize_enum_type_node(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref decl,
7102 scope_ptr scope);
7103
7104static int
7105is_constant_expr(sm_ref expr)
7106{
7107 switch(expr->node_type) {
7108 case cod_constant: {
7109 return 1;
7110 break;
7111 }
7112 case cod_identifier:
7113 if (!expr->node.identifier.sm_declaration) return 0;
7114 return is_constant_expr(expr->node.identifier.sm_declaration);
7115 case cod_declaration:
7116 if (!expr->node.declaration.const_var) return 0;
7117 return is_constant_expr(expr->node.declaration.init_value);
7118 case cod_operator: {
7119 long left, right;
7120 if (expr->node.operator.left != NULL((void*)0)) {
7121 if (!is_constant_expr(expr->node.operator.left)) return 0;
7122 }
7123 if (expr->node.operator.op == op_sizeof) {
7124 return 1;
7125 }
7126 if (expr->node.operator.right != NULL((void*)0)) {
7127 if (!is_constant_expr(expr->node.operator.right)) return 0;
7128 }
7129 switch(expr->node.operator.op) {
7130 case op_modulus:
7131 case op_not:
7132 case op_plus:
7133 case op_minus:
7134 case op_leq:
7135 case op_lt:
7136 case op_geq:
7137 case op_gt:
7138 case op_eq:
7139 case op_neq:
7140 case op_log_or:
7141 case op_arith_or:
7142 case op_arith_xor:
7143 case op_log_and:
7144 case op_arith_and:
7145 case op_mult:
7146 case op_div:
7147 case op_log_neg:
7148 case op_left_shift:
7149 case op_right_shift:
7150 return 1;
7151 break;
7152 case op_deref:
7153 case op_address:
7154 case op_inc:
7155 case op_dec:
7156 case op_sizeof:
7157 return 0;
7158 }
7159 return 1;
7160 }
7161 case cod_cast:
7162 return is_constant_expr(expr->node.cast.expression);
7163 case cod_assignment_expression:
7164 case cod_field_ref:
7165 case cod_element_ref:
7166 case cod_subroutine_call:
7167 return 0;
7168 default:
7169 assert(0)((void) sizeof ((0) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (0) ; else __assert_fail
("0", "cod/cod.y", 4904, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__);
}));
7170 }
7171 return 0;
7172}
7173
7174static int
7175possibly_set_sizes_to_match(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref decl, sm_ref init_value)
7176{
7177 sm_ref array_type = get_complex_type(context, decl);
7178 if (array_type->node.array_type_decl.size_expr) return 1;
7179 if ((init_value->node_type == cod_constant) &&
7180 (init_value->node.constant.token == string_constant)) {
7181 /* init value is a string, set the array size to strlen + 1 */
7182 sm_ref size_expr = cod_new_constant();
7183 char *str = malloc(20); /* plenty */
7184 size_expr->node.constant.token = integer_constant;
7185 sprintf(str, "%ld\n", (long) strlen(init_value->node.constant.const_val) + 1);
7186 size_expr->node.constant.const_val = str;
7187 array_type->node.array_type_decl.size_expr = size_expr;
7188 return 1;
7189 }
7190
7191 if (is_array(decl)) {
7192 sm_list items;
7193 long size = 0;
7194 assert(init_value->node_type == cod_initializer_list)((void) sizeof ((init_value->node_type == cod_initializer_list
) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (init_value->node_type == cod_initializer_list
) ; else __assert_fail ("init_value->node_type == cod_initializer_list"
, "cod/cod.y", 4929, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
7195 items = init_value->node.initializer_list.initializers;
7196 /* init value is a list of initializers, count */
7197 while (items) {
7198 size++;
7199 items = items->next;
7200 }
7201 sm_ref size_expr = cod_new_constant();
7202 char *str = malloc(20); /* plenty */
7203 size_expr->node.constant.token = integer_constant;
7204 sprintf(str, "%ld\n", size);
7205 size_expr->node.constant.const_val = str;
7206 array_type->node.array_type_decl.size_expr = size_expr;
7207 return 1;
7208 }
7209 printf("Decl is : \n"); cod_print(decl);
7210 printf("init_value is : \n"); cod_print(init_value);
7211 return 1;
7212}
7213static int semanticize_decl(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref decl,
7214 scope_ptr scope)
7215{
7216 switch(decl->node_type) {
7217 case cod_declaration: {
7218 sm_ref ctype;
7219 int is_block_type = 0;
7220
7221 if (resolve_local(decl->node.declaration.id, scope) != NULL((void*)0)) {
7222 if (resolve_local(decl->node.declaration.id, scope) != decl) {
7223 cod_src_error(context, decl, "Duplicate Symbol \"%s\"",
7224 decl->node.declaration.id);
7225 return 0;
7226 } else {
7227 /* been here, done that */
7228 return 1;
7229 }
7230 } else {
7231 add_decl(decl->node.declaration.id, decl, scope);
7232 }
7233 if (scope->containing_scope == NULL((void*)0)) {
7234 /* must be external variable */
7235 void *extern_value =
7236 resolve_extern(decl->node.declaration.id, scope);
7237 if ((extern_value == NULL((void*)0)) && (context->alloc_globals)) {
7238 ;
7239 } else if ((extern_value == NULL((void*)0)) && (decl->node.declaration.cg_address == NULL((void*)0)) &&
7240 (decl->node.declaration.const_var == 0)) {
7241 cod_src_error(context, decl,
7242 "External symbol lacking address \"%s\"",
7243 decl->node.declaration.id);
7244 return 0;
7245 }
7246 if (extern_value) {
7247 decl->node.declaration.cg_address = extern_value;
7248 }
7249 decl->node.declaration.is_extern = 1;
7250 }
7251 if (decl->node.declaration.type_spec != NULL((void*)0)) {
7252 sm_list l = decl->node.declaration.type_spec;
7253 if ((l->node->node_type == cod_type_specifier) &&
7254 ((l->node->node.type_specifier.token == STATIC) ||
7255 (l->node->node.type_specifier.token == CONST))) {
7256 if ((l->node->node.type_specifier.token == STATIC) &&
7257 !decl->node.declaration.is_subroutine) {
7258 decl->node.declaration.static_var = 1;
7259 } else {
7260 decl->node.declaration.const_var = 1;
7261 }
7262 decl->node.declaration.type_spec = l->next;
7263 free(l->node);
7264 free(l);
7265 }
7266 }
7267 if (decl->node.declaration.static_var) {
7268 if (decl->node.declaration.init_value != NULL((void*)0)) {
7269 sm_ref const_val = decl->node.declaration.init_value;
7270 if (const_val->node_type == cod_initializer_list) {
7271 sm_list items = const_val->node.initializer_list.initializers;
7272 /* init value is a list of initializers, count */
7273 while (items) {
7274 sm_ref sub_init = items->node->node.initializer.initializer;
7275 if (!is_constant_expr(sub_init)) {
7276 cod_src_error(context, sub_init,
7277 "Static initializer not constant. Variable \"%s\"",
7278 decl->node.declaration.id);
7279 return 0;
7280 }
7281 items = items->next;
7282 }
7283
7284 } else if (!is_constant_expr(const_val)) {
7285 cod_src_error(context, const_val,
7286 "Static initializer not constant. Variable \"%s\"",
7287 decl->node.declaration.id);
7288 return 0;
7289 }
7290 }
7291 }
7292 if ((decl->node.declaration.sm_complex_type != NULL((void*)0)) &&
7293 (decl->node.declaration.param_num != -1)) {
7294 /* complex type + param, must be pass by reference */
7295 sm_ref type = decl->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
7296 decl->node.declaration.cg_type = DILL_P;
7297 if (type->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
7298 int ret = semanticize_array_type_node(context, type,
7299 scope);
7300 if (ret == 0) return ret;
7301 }
7302 }
7303 /* some array decls have sm_complex_type set already */
7304 if (decl->node.declaration.sm_complex_type == NULL((void*)0)) {
7305 sm_ref typ = NULL((void*)0);
7306 int cg_type = DILL_I;
7307 if (decl->node.declaration.type_spec != NULL((void*)0)) {
7308 int type_def = 0;
7309 typ = reduce_type_list(context, decl->node.declaration.type_spec,
7310 &cg_type, scope, &type_def, &decl->node.declaration.freeable_complex_type);
7311 if (type_def) {
7312 decl->node.declaration.is_typedef = 1;
7313 }
7314 } else {
7315 sm_ref arr = decl->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
7316 if ((arr != NULL((void*)0)) &&
7317 (arr->node_type == cod_array_type_decl)) {
7318 typ = reduce_type_list(context,
7319 arr->node.array_type_decl.type_spec,
7320 &cg_type, scope, NULL((void*)0), &decl->node.declaration.freeable_complex_type);
7321 } else if ((arr != NULL((void*)0)) && (arr->node_type == cod_enum_type_decl)) {
7322 cg_type = DILL_I;
7323 }
7324 }
7325 if ((typ == NULL((void*)0)) && (cg_type == DILL_ERR)) return 0;
7326 decl->node.declaration.cg_type = cg_type;
7327 decl->node.declaration.sm_complex_type = typ;
7328 }
7329 ctype = decl->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
7330 if ((ctype != NULL((void*)0)) && ((ctype->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) || (ctype->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl))) {
7331 is_block_type = 1;
7332 }
7333 if (decl->node.declaration.init_value != NULL((void*)0)) {
7334 int ret;
7335 ret = semanticize_expr(context, decl->node.declaration.init_value,
7336 scope);
7337 if (ret == 0) return ret;
7338 if (is_array(decl)) {
7339 ret = possibly_set_sizes_to_match(context, decl, decl->node.declaration.init_value);
7340 }
7341 ret = assignment_types_match(context, decl,
7342 decl->node.declaration.init_value, 1);
7343 return ret;
7344 }
7345 if (decl->node.declaration.is_subroutine) {
7346 int ret;
7347 int param_count = 0;
7348 sm_list params = decl->node.declaration.params;
7349 scope_ptr sub_scope = push_scope(scope);
7350 ret = semanticize_decls_list(context,
7351 decl->node.declaration.params,
7352 sub_scope);
7353 decl->node.declaration.varidiac_subroutine_param_count = -1;
7354 while(params) {
7355 sm_ref formal = params->node;
7356 while(formal->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
7357 formal = formal->node.array_type_decl.element_ref;
7358 }
7359 if (strcmp(formal->node.declaration.id, "...") == 0) {
7360 decl->node.declaration.varidiac_subroutine_param_count = param_count;
7361 }
7362 params = params->next;
7363 param_count++;
7364 }
7365 pop_scope(sub_scope);
7366 return ret;
7367 }
7368 return 1;
7369 break;
7370 }
7371 case cod_struct_type_decl:
7372 return semanticize_struct_type_node(context, decl, scope);
7373 break;
7374 case cod_array_type_decl:
7375 if (decl->node.array_type_decl.type_spec != NULL((void*)0)) {
7376 sm_list l = decl->node.array_type_decl.type_spec;
7377 if ((l->node->node_type == cod_type_specifier) &&
7378 (l->node->node.type_specifier.token == STATIC)) {
7379 decl->node.array_type_decl.type_spec = l->next;
7380 decl->node.array_type_decl.element_ref->node.declaration.static_var = 1;
7381 free(l->node);
7382 free(l);
7383 }
7384 }
7385 return semanticize_array_type_node(context, decl, scope);
7386 break;
7387 case cod_reference_type_decl:
7388 return semanticize_reference_type_node(context, decl, scope);
7389 break;
7390 case cod_constant:
7391 return 1;
7392 break;
7393 case cod_enum_type_decl:
7394 return semanticize_enum_type_node(context, decl, scope);
7395 break;
7396 default:
7397 printf("Unhandled case in semanticize decls_list\n");
7398 cod_print(decl);
7399 }
7400 return 0;
7401}
7402
7403static int semanticize_statement(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref stmt,
7404 scope_ptr scope);
7405static int
7406check_last_statement_return_list(cod_parse_context context, sm_list stmts);
7407
7408static int
7409check_last_statement_return(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref stmt)
7410{
7411 switch (stmt->node_type) {
7412 case cod_selection_statement:
7413 if (!check_last_statement_return(context, stmt->node.selection_statement.then_part)) return 0;
7414 if (stmt->node.selection_statement.else_part &&
7415 !check_last_statement_return(context, stmt->node.selection_statement.else_part)) return 0;
7416 return 1;
7417 case cod_compound_statement: {
7418 sm_list list = stmt->node.compound_statement.statements;
7419 if (!list) list = stmt->node.compound_statement.decls;
7420 if (list) return check_last_statement_return_list(context, list);
7421 return 1;
7422 }
7423 case cod_return_statement:
7424 return 1;
7425 case cod_expression_statement:
7426 return check_last_statement_return(context, stmt->node.expression_statement.expression);
7427 case cod_label_statement:
7428 return check_last_statement_return(context, stmt->node.label_statement.statement);
7429 case cod_subroutine_call: {
7430 sm_ref func_ref = stmt->node.subroutine_call.sm_func_ref;
7431 char *id;
7432 if (func_ref->node_type == cod_identifier) {
7433 id = func_ref->node.identifier.id;
7434 } else {
7435 id = func_ref->node.declaration.id;
7436 }
7437 if (strcmp(id, "exit") == 0) return 1;
7438 if (strcmp(id, "abort") == 0) return 1;
7439 return 0;
7440 }
7441 default:
7442 return 0;
7443 }
7444}
7445
7446static int
7447check_last_statement_return_list(cod_parse_context context, sm_list stmts)
7448{
7449 sm_ref stmt;
7450 while (stmts != NULL((void*)0)) {
7451 stmt = stmts->node;
7452 stmts = stmts->next;
7453 }
7454 if (!stmt) return 0;
7455 return check_last_statement_return(context, stmt);
7456}
7457
7458static int
7459semanticize_decls_stmts_list(cod_parse_context context, sm_list decls_stmts, scope_ptr scope)
7460{
7461 int ret = 1;
7462 while (decls_stmts != NULL((void*)0)) {
7463 sm_ref item = decls_stmts->node;
7464 switch(item->node_type) {
7465 case cod_declaration:
7466 case cod_struct_type_decl:
7467 case cod_array_type_decl:
7468 case cod_reference_type_decl:
7469 case cod_enum_type_decl:
7470 case cod_constant:
7471 if (!semanticize_decl(context, item, scope)) {
7472 ret = 0;
7473 }
7474 break;
7475 default: {
7476 int t = semanticize_statement(context, item, scope);
7477 if (!t) {
7478 ret = 0;
7479 }
7480 }
7481 }
7482 decls_stmts = decls_stmts->next;
7483 }
7484 return ret;
7485}
7486
7487static int
7488semanticize_decls_list(cod_parse_context context, sm_list decls,
7489 scope_ptr scope)
7490{
7491 int ret = 1;
7492 while (decls != NULL((void*)0)) {
7493 if (!semanticize_decl(context, decls->node, scope)) {
7494 ret = 0;
7495 }
7496 decls = decls->next;
7497 }
7498 return ret;
7499}
7500
7501static int
7502semanticize_selection_statement(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref selection,
7503 scope_ptr scope)
7504{
7505 int ret = 1;
7506 if (!semanticize_expr(context,
7507 selection->node.selection_statement.conditional,
7508 scope)) {
7509 ret = 0;
7510 }
7511 if (!semanticize_statement(context,
7512 selection->node.selection_statement.then_part,
7513 scope)) {
7514 ret = 0;
7515 }
7516 if (selection->node.selection_statement.else_part) {
7517 if (!semanticize_statement(context,
7518 selection->node.selection_statement.else_part,
7519 scope)) {
7520 ret = 0;
7521 }
7522 }
7523 return ret;
7524}
7525
7526static int
7527semanticize_iteration_statement(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref iteration,
7528 scope_ptr scope)
7529{
7530 int ret = 1;
7531 if (iteration->node.iteration_statement.init_expr != NULL((void*)0)) {
7532 if (!semanticize_expr(context,
7533 iteration->node.iteration_statement.init_expr,
7534 scope)) {
7535 ret = 0;
7536 }
7537 }
7538
7539 if (iteration->node.iteration_statement.test_expr != NULL((void*)0)) {
7540 if (!semanticize_expr(context,
7541 iteration->node.iteration_statement.test_expr,
7542 scope)) {
7543 ret = 0;
7544 }
7545 }
7546
7547 if (iteration->node.iteration_statement.iter_expr != NULL((void*)0)) {
7548 if (!semanticize_expr(context,
7549 iteration->node.iteration_statement.iter_expr,
7550 scope)) {
7551 ret = 0;
7552 }
7553 }
7554
7555 if (iteration->node.iteration_statement.statement != NULL((void*)0)) {
7556 scope_ptr sub_scope = push_scope_container(scope, iteration);
7557 if (!semanticize_statement(context,
7558 iteration->node.iteration_statement.statement,
7559 sub_scope)) {
7560 ret = 0;
7561 }
7562 pop_scope(sub_scope);
7563 }
7564 if (iteration->node.iteration_statement.post_test_expr != NULL((void*)0)) {
7565 if (!semanticize_expr(context,
7566 iteration->node.iteration_statement.post_test_expr,
7567 scope)) {
7568 ret = 0;
7569 }
7570 }
7571
7572 return ret;
7573}
7574
7575static int
7576semanticize_statement(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref stmt,
7577 scope_ptr scope)
7578{
7579 if (!stmt) return 1;
7580 switch (stmt->node_type) {
7581 case cod_selection_statement:
7582 return semanticize_selection_statement(context, stmt, scope);
7583 case cod_iteration_statement:
7584 return semanticize_iteration_statement(context, stmt, scope);
7585 case cod_expression_statement: {
7586 return semanticize_expr(context,
7587 stmt->node.expression_statement.expression,
7588 scope);
7589 }
7590 case cod_compound_statement:
7591 return semanticize_compound_statement(context, stmt, scope, 0);
7592 case cod_return_statement:{
7593 int expr_type;
7594 stmt->node.return_statement.cg_func_type = context->return_cg_type;
7595 if (stmt->node.return_statement.cg_func_type == DILL_V) {
7596 if (stmt->node.return_statement.expression != NULL((void*)0)) {
7597 cod_src_error(context, stmt,
7598 "Return value supplied in subroutine declared to return VOID");
7599 return 0;
7600 }
7601 } else {
7602 if (stmt->node.return_statement.expression == NULL((void*)0)) {
7603 cod_src_error(context, stmt,
7604 "Return value missing in non-VOID subroutine");
7605 return 0;
7606 }
7607 }
7608 if (stmt->node.return_statement.expression == NULL((void*)0)) return 1;
7609 if (!semanticize_expr(context, stmt->node.return_statement.expression,
7610 scope)) return 0;
7611 expr_type = cod_sm_get_type(stmt->node.return_statement.expression);
7612 if (context->dont_coerce_return) {
7613 int type_failure = 0;
7614 switch (stmt->node.return_statement.cg_func_type) {
7615 case DILL_C: case DILL_UC: case DILL_S: case DILL_US: case DILL_I: case DILL_U: case DILL_L: case DILL_UL:
7616 if (expr_type > DILL_UL) type_failure++;
7617 break;
7618 case DILL_F: case DILL_D:
7619 if ((expr_type != DILL_F) && (expr_type != DILL_D)) type_failure++;
7620 break;
7621 }
7622 if (type_failure) {
7623 cod_src_error(context, stmt,
7624 "Return value doesn't match procedure type declaration and now allowed to use coercion");
7625 return 0;
7626 }
7627 }
7628 return 1;
7629 }
7630 case cod_label_statement:{
7631// add_decl(stmt->node.label_statement.name, stmt, scope);
7632 return semanticize_statement(context, stmt->node.label_statement.statement, scope);
7633 }
7634 case cod_jump_statement:{
7635 if (stmt->node.jump_statement.goto_target != NULL((void*)0)) {
7636 if (!stmt->node.jump_statement.sm_target_stmt) {
7637 cod_src_error(context, stmt,
7638 "Label \"%s\" not found. Goto has no target.", stmt->node.jump_statement.goto_target);
7639 return 0;
7640 }
7641 } else {
7642 /* this is a continue or a break */
7643 sm_ref tmp = find_containing_iterator(scope);
7644 if (!tmp) {
7645 cod_src_error(context, stmt,
7646 "Continue or Break statement not contained inside an iterator.");
7647 return 0;
7648 }
7649 stmt->node.jump_statement.sm_target_stmt = tmp;
7650 }
7651 return 1;
7652 break;
7653 }
7654 default:
7655 printf("unhandled case in semanticize statement\n");
7656 return 1;
7657 }
7658 return 1;
7659}
7660
7661typedef struct goto_semantic_state {
7662 int backward_jump;
7663 int passed_init_decl;
7664 int already_found;
7665} *goto_state;
7666
7667static int semanticize_goto_l(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref this_goto, sm_list stmts, goto_state gs);
7668
7669static int semanticize_goto(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref this_goto, sm_ref stmt, goto_state gs)
7670{
7671 int ret = 1;
7672 if (!stmt) return ret;
7673 switch (stmt->node_type) {
7674 case cod_declaration:
7675 if (!gs->backward_jump && stmt->node.declaration.init_value) {
7676 gs->passed_init_decl = 1;
7677 }
7678 break;
7679 case cod_struct_type_decl:
7680 case cod_array_type_decl:
7681 case cod_reference_type_decl:
7682 case cod_enum_type_decl:
7683 case cod_constant:
7684 /* no action for decls */
7685 break;
7686 case cod_selection_statement:
7687 ret &= semanticize_goto(context, this_goto, stmt->node.selection_statement.then_part, gs);
7688 if (stmt->node.selection_statement.else_part)
7689 ret &= semanticize_goto(context, this_goto, stmt->node.selection_statement.else_part, gs);
7690 break;
7691 case cod_iteration_statement:
7692 ret &= semanticize_goto(context, this_goto, stmt->node.iteration_statement.statement, gs);
7693 break;
7694 case cod_compound_statement:
7695 ret &= semanticize_goto_l(context, this_goto, stmt->node.compound_statement.decls, gs);
7696 ret &= semanticize_goto_l(context, this_goto, stmt->node.compound_statement.statements, gs);
7697 break;
7698 case cod_return_statement:
7699 break;
7700 case cod_label_statement:
7701 if (strcmp(this_goto->node.jump_statement.goto_target, stmt->node.label_statement.name) == 0) {
7702 /* found target */
7703 if (!gs->backward_jump && gs->passed_init_decl) {
7704 cod_src_error(context, stmt, "Goto jumps over initialized declaration, illegal forward jump.");
7705 ret = 0;
7706 } else if (gs->already_found) {
7707 cod_src_error(context, stmt, "Duplicate label \"%s\".", stmt->node.label_statement.name);
7708 ret = 0;
7709 } else {
7710 this_goto->node.jump_statement.sm_target_stmt = stmt;
7711 gs->already_found = 1;
7712 }
7713 }
7714 ret &= semanticize_goto(context, this_goto, stmt->node.label_statement.statement, gs);
7715 break;
7716 case cod_jump_statement:
7717 if (stmt == this_goto) {
7718 gs->backward_jump = 0;
7719 }
7720 break;
7721 case cod_expression_statement:
7722 break;
7723 default:
7724 printf("unhandled case in semanticize goto\n");
7725 return 0;
7726 }
7727 return ret;
7728}
7729
7730static int semanticize_goto_l(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref this_goto, sm_list stmts, goto_state gs)
7731{
7732 int saved_passed_init_decl = gs->passed_init_decl;
7733 int ret = 1;
7734 while(stmts) {
7735 ret &= semanticize_goto(context, this_goto, stmts->node, gs);
7736 stmts = stmts->next;
7737 }
7738 gs->passed_init_decl = saved_passed_init_decl;
7739 return ret;
7740}
7741
7742static int
7743semanticize_gotos_list(cod_parse_context context, sm_list stmts, sm_list function_context)
7744{
7745 int ret = 1;
7746 while(stmts) {
7747 ret &= semanticize_gotos(context, stmts->node, function_context);
7748 stmts = stmts->next;
7749 }
7750 return ret;
7751}
7752
7753static int
7754semanticize_gotos(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref stmt, sm_list function_context)
7755{
7756 /*
7757 * recursive descent looking for goto's, followed by a recursive descent in
7758 * the entire scope looking for their target
7759 */
7760 int ret = 1;
7761 if (!stmt) return 1;
7762 switch (stmt->node_type) {
7763 case cod_declaration:
7764 case cod_struct_type_decl:
7765 case cod_array_type_decl:
7766 case cod_reference_type_decl:
7767 case cod_enum_type_decl:
7768 case cod_constant:
7769 /* no action for most decls */
7770 break;
7771 case cod_selection_statement:
7772 ret &= semanticize_gotos(context, stmt->node.selection_statement.then_part, function_context);
7773 if (stmt->node.selection_statement.else_part)
7774 ret &= semanticize_gotos(context, stmt->node.selection_statement.else_part, function_context);
7775 break;
7776 case cod_iteration_statement:
7777 ret &= semanticize_gotos(context, stmt->node.iteration_statement.statement, function_context);
7778 break;
7779 case cod_compound_statement:
7780 ret &= semanticize_gotos_list(context, stmt->node.compound_statement.decls, function_context);
7781 ret &= semanticize_gotos_list(context, stmt->node.compound_statement.statements, function_context);
7782 break;
7783 case cod_return_statement:
7784 break;
7785 case cod_label_statement:
7786 ret &= semanticize_gotos(context, stmt->node.label_statement.statement, function_context);
7787 break;
7788 case cod_jump_statement:
7789 if (stmt->node.jump_statement.goto_target != NULL((void*)0)) {
7790 /* this is a goto */
7791 struct goto_semantic_state gs;
7792 gs.backward_jump = 1;
7793 gs.passed_init_decl = 0;
7794 gs.already_found = 0;
7795 ret &= semanticize_goto_l(context, stmt, function_context, &gs);
7796 }
7797 break;
7798 case cod_expression_statement:
7799 break;
7800 default:
7801 printf("unhandled case in semanticize gotos\n");
7802 return 0;
7803 }
7804 return ret;
7805}
7806
7807extern int
7808semanticize_compound_statement(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref compound,
7809 scope_ptr containing_scope, int require_last_return)
7810{
7811 int ret = 1;
7812 scope_ptr current_scope = push_scope(containing_scope);
7813
7814 ret &= semanticize_decls_stmts_list(context,
7815 compound->node.compound_statement.decls,
7816 current_scope);
7817 ret &= semanticize_decls_stmts_list(context,
7818 compound->node.compound_statement.statements,
7819 current_scope);
7820 if (ret && require_last_return) {
7821 int tmp;
7822 sm_list list = compound->node.compound_statement.statements;
7823 if (!list) list = compound->node.compound_statement.decls;
7824 tmp = check_last_statement_return_list(context, compound->node.compound_statement.statements);
7825 if (!tmp) {
7826 cod_src_error(context, NULL((void*)0),
7827 "Control reaches end of non-void function.");
7828 }
7829 ret &= tmp;
7830 }
7831 pop_scope(current_scope);
7832 return ret;
7833}
7834
7835extern sm_ref
7836cod_build_type_node(const char *name, FMFieldList field_list)
7837{
7838 sm_ref decl = cod_new_struct_type_decl();
7839 sm_list *end_ptr = &decl->node.struct_type_decl.fields;
7840
7841 decl->node.struct_type_decl.id = strdup(name);
7842 while ((field_list != NULL((void*)0)) && (field_list->field_name != NULL((void*)0))) {
7843 sm_list new_elem;
7844 new_elem = malloc(sizeof(*new_elem));
7845 new_elem->next = NULL((void*)0);
7846 new_elem->node = cod_new_field();
7847 new_elem->node->node.field.name = strdup(field_list->field_name);
7848 new_elem->node->node.field.string_type = strdup(field_list->field_type);
7849 new_elem->node->node.field.cg_size = field_list->field_size;
7850 new_elem->node->node.field.cg_offset = field_list->field_offset;
7851 new_elem->node->node.field.cg_type = DILL_ERR;
7852 *end_ptr = new_elem;
7853 end_ptr = &new_elem->next;
7854 field_list++;
7855 }
7856 return decl;
7857}

7859
7860extern void
7861cod_remove_defined_types(cod_parse_context context, int count)
7862{
7863 char **types = context->defined_types;
7864 while(types && types[count]) types[count++] = NULL((void*)0);
7865}
7866
7867void
7868cod_add_defined_type(id, context)
7869char *id;
7870cod_parse_context context;
7871{
7872 int count = 0;
7873 while(context->defined_types && context->defined_types[count]) count++;
7874 if (count == 0) {
7875 context->defined_types = malloc(sizeof(char*) * 2);
7876 } else {
7877 context->defined_types = realloc(context->defined_types,
7878 (count+2)*sizeof(char*));
7879 }
7880 context->defined_types[count] = id;
7881 context->defined_types[count+1] = NULL((void*)0);
7882 reset_types_table(context->defined_types, context->enumerated_constants);
7883
7884}
7885
7886void
7887cod_add_enum_const(id, context)
7888char *id;
7889cod_parse_context context;
7890{
7891 int count = 0;
7892 while(context->enumerated_constants && context->enumerated_constants[count]) count++;
7893 if (count == 0) {
7894 context->enumerated_constants = malloc(sizeof(char*) * 2);
7895 } else {
7896 context->enumerated_constants = realloc(context->enumerated_constants,
7897 (count+2)*sizeof(char*));
7898 }
7899 context->enumerated_constants[count] = id;
7900 context->enumerated_constants[count+1] = NULL((void*)0);
7901 reset_types_table(context->defined_types, context->enumerated_constants);
7902}
7903
7904extern void
7905cod_add_simple_struct_type(const char *name, FMFieldList field_list,
7906 cod_parse_context context)
7907{
7908 sm_ref node = cod_build_type_node(name, field_list);
7909 cod_add_decl_to_parse_context(name, node, context);
7910 cod_add_decl_to_scope((char*)name, node, context);
7911}
7912
7913extern void
7914cod_add_struct_type(FMStructDescList format_list,
7915 cod_parse_context context)
7916{
7917 int count=0;
7918 while(format_list && format_list[count].format_name) {
7919 count++;
7920 }
7921 count = count-1;
7922 for ( ; count >= 0; count--) {
7923 cod_add_simple_struct_type(format_list[count].format_name,
7924 format_list[count].field_list,
7925 context);
7926 }
7927}
7928
7929static int
7930str_to_data_type(str, size)
7931char *str;
7932int size;
7933{
7934 char *tmp = malloc(strlen(str) + 1);
7935 char *free_str = tmp;
7936 strcpy(tmp, str);
7937 str = tmp; /* make a copy of str parameter */
7938
7939 while (isspace((int)*str)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) (((int)*str))] & (unsigned short
int) _ISspace) || (*str == '*') || (*str == '(')) { /* skip preceeding space */
7940 str++;
7941 }
7942 tmp = str + strlen(str) - 1;
7943 while (isspace((int)*tmp)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) (((int)*tmp))] & (unsigned short
int) _ISspace) || (*tmp == ')')) { /* test trailing space */
7944 *tmp = 0;
7945 tmp--;
7946 }
7947 tmp = str;
7948 while (*tmp) { /* map to lower case */
7949 *tmp = tolower(*tmp);
7950 tmp++;
7951 }
7952 if ((strcmp(str, "integer") == 0) || (strcmp(str, "enumeration") == 0)) {
7953 free(free_str);
7954 if (size == sizeof(long)) {
7955 return DILL_L;
7956 } else if (size == sizeof(int)) {
7957 return DILL_I;
7958 } else if (size == sizeof(short)) {
7959 return DILL_S;
7960 } else if (size == sizeof(char)) {
7961 return DILL_C;
7962 } else {
7963 return DILL_L;
7964 }
7965 } else if (strcmp(str, "unsigned integer") == 0) {
7966 free(free_str);
7967 if (size == sizeof(long)) {
7968 return DILL_UL;
7969 } else if (size == sizeof(int)) {
7970 return DILL_U;
7971 } else if (size == sizeof(short)) {
7972 return DILL_US;
7973 } else if (size == sizeof(char)) {
7974 return DILL_UC;
7975 } else {
7976 return DILL_UL;
7977 }
7978 } else if ((strcmp(str, "float") == 0) || (strcmp(str, "double") == 0)) {
7979 free(free_str);
7980 if (size == sizeof(double)) {
7981 return DILL_D;
7982 } else if (size == sizeof(float)) {
7983 return DILL_F;
7984 } else {
7985 fprintf(stderrstderr, "unsupported float size %d\n", size);
7986 return DILL_D;
7987 }
7988 } else if (strcmp(str, "char") == 0) {
7989 free(free_str);
7990 assert(size == 1)((void) sizeof ((size == 1) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (size
== 1) ; else __assert_fail ("size == 1", "cod/cod.y", 5725, __extension__
__PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
7991 return DILL_C;
7992 } else if (strcmp(str, "string") == 0) {
7993 free(free_str);
7994 return DILL_P;
7995 } else {
7996 free(free_str);
7997 return DILL_ERR;
7998 }
7999}
8000
8001static int
8002array_str_to_data_type(str, size)
8003char *str;
8004int size;
8005{
8006 int ret_type;
8007 char field_type[1024];
8008 char *left_paren;
8009 if ((left_paren = strchr(str, '[')) == NULL((void*)0)) {
8010 ret_type = str_to_data_type(str, size);
8011 } else {
8012 char *tmp = str;
8013 int i = 0;
8014 for( ; tmp < left_paren; tmp++) {
8015 field_type[i++] = *tmp;
8016 }
8017 field_type[i] = 0;
8018 ret_type = str_to_data_type(field_type, size);
8019 }
8020 return ret_type;
8021}
8022
8023static sm_ref
8024build_subtype_nodes(context, decl, f, desc, err, scope, must_free_p)
8025cod_parse_context context;
8026sm_ref decl;
8027field* f;
8028FMTypeDesc *desc;
8029int *err;
8030scope_ptr scope;
8031int *must_free_p;
8032{
8033 sm_ref ret = NULL((void*)0);
8034 sm_ref subtype = NULL((void*)0);
8035 int must_free_flag = 0;
8036 if (desc->next != NULL((void*)0)) {
8037 subtype = build_subtype_nodes(context, decl, f, desc->next, err, scope, &must_free_flag);
8038 if (*err != 0) {
8039 printf("Subtype node failure\n");
8040 return NULL((void*)0);
8041 }
8042 }
8043 switch (desc->type) {
8044 case FMType_array: {
8045 sm_list fields = decl->node.struct_type_decl.fields;
8046 sm_ref cf;
8047 int i;
8048 ret = cod_new_array_type_decl();
8049 *must_free_p = 1;
8050 ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_static_size = desc->static_size;
8051 if (desc->static_size == 0) {
8052 ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_static_size = -1;
8053 }
8054 ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_type = DILL_B;
8055 ret->node.array_type_decl.sm_complex_element_type = subtype;
8056 if (must_free_flag) {
8057 if (ret->node.array_type_decl.freeable_complex_element_type) {
8058 cod_rfree(ret->node.array_type_decl.freeable_complex_element_type);
8059 }
8060 ret->node.array_type_decl.freeable_complex_element_type = subtype;
8061 }
8062 if (subtype == NULL((void*)0)) {
8063 ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_type =
8064 array_str_to_data_type(f->string_type, f->cg_size);
8065 ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_size = f->cg_size;
8066 ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions = malloc(sizeof(struct dimen_p));
8067 ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimen_count = 1;
8068 } else {
8069 if (subtype->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
8070 int sub_size = subtype->node.array_type_decl.cg_static_size;
8071 int sub_dimensions = subtype->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimen_count;
8072 if (sub_size == -1) {
8073 /* element of *this* array has varying elements */
8074 ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_size = -1;
8075 } else {
8076 ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_size =
8077 sub_size * subtype->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_size;;
8078 }
8079
8080 ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions = malloc(sizeof(struct dimen_p) + sub_dimensions * sizeof(dimen_s));
8081 ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimen_count = sub_dimensions+1;;
8082 memcpy(&ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimens[1], &subtype->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimens[0], sub_dimensions * sizeof(dimen_s));
8083 } else {
8084 ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_size = f->cg_size;
8085 ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions = malloc(sizeof(struct dimen_p));
8086 ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimen_count = 1;
8087 if (subtype->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
8088 ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_type = DILL_P;
8089 }
8090 }
8091 }
8092
8093 if (ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_static_size != -1) {
8094 ret->node.array_type_decl.sm_dynamic_size = NULL((void*)0);
8095 ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimens[0].static_size = ret->node.array_type_decl.cg_static_size;
8096 ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimens[0].control_field = NULL((void*)0);
8097 } else {
8098 for (i=0; i < desc->control_field_index; i++) {
8099 fields = fields->next;
8100 }
8101 cf = fields->node;
8102 switch (str_to_data_type(cf->node.field.string_type,
8103 (int)sizeof(int))) {
8104 case DILL_C: case DILL_UC: case DILL_S: case DILL_US:
8105 case DILL_I: case DILL_U: case DILL_L: case DILL_UL:
8106 break;
8107 default:
8108 cod_src_error(context, NULL((void*)0),
8109 "Variable length control field \"%s\"not of integer type.", cf->node.field.string_type);
8110 *err = 1;
8111 return NULL((void*)0);
8112 break;
8113 }
8114 ret->node.array_type_decl.sm_dynamic_size = cf;
8115 ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimens[0].static_size = -1;
8116 ret->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimens[0].control_field = cf;
8117 }
8118 break;
8119 }
8120 case FMType_pointer:
8121 ret = cod_new_reference_type_decl();
8122 *must_free_p = 1;
8123 ret->node.reference_type_decl.name = gen_anon();
8124 ret->node.reference_type_decl.cg_referenced_type = DILL_ERR;
8125 ret->node.reference_type_decl.sm_complex_referenced_type = subtype;
8126 if (must_free_flag) {
8127 if (ret->node.array_type_decl.freeable_complex_element_type) {
8128 cod_rfree(ret->node.array_type_decl.freeable_complex_element_type);
8129 }
8130 ret->node.reference_type_decl.freeable_complex_referenced_type = subtype;
8131 }
8132 ret->node.reference_type_decl.cg_referenced_size = -1;
8133 break;
8134 case FMType_subformat: {
8135 char *tmp_str = FMbase_type(f->string_type);
8136 ret = resolve(tmp_str, scope);
8137 free(tmp_str);
8138 if (ret == NULL((void*)0)) {
8139 printf("Didn't find base type %s\n", tmp_str);
8140 *err = 1;
8141 }
8142 break;
8143 }
8144 case FMType_simple:
8145 case FMType_string:
8146 ret = NULL((void*)0);
8147 break;
8148 }
8149 return ret;
8150
8151}
8152
8153static void
8154build_type_nodes(context, decl, f, fields, cg_size, cg_type, desc, err, scope)
8155cod_parse_context context;
8156sm_ref decl;
8157field* f;
8158sm_list fields;
8159int cg_size;
8160int cg_type;
8161FMTypeDesc* desc;
8162int *err;
8163scope_ptr scope;
8164{
8165 int must_free_flag = 0;
8166 sm_ref complex_type = build_subtype_nodes(context, decl, f, desc, err, scope, &must_free_flag);
8167 f->sm_complex_type = complex_type;
8168 if (must_free_flag) {
8169 if (f->freeable_complex_type) {
8170 cod_rfree(f->freeable_complex_type);
8171 }
8172 f->freeable_complex_type = complex_type;
8173 }
8174}
8175
8176static int
8177semanticize_array_element_node(context, array, super_type, base_type_spec,
8178 scope)
8179cod_parse_context context;
8180sm_ref array;
8181sm_ref super_type;
8182sm_list base_type_spec;
8183scope_ptr scope;
8184{
8185 if (array->node.array_type_decl.size_expr != NULL((void*)0)) {
8186 if (!is_constant_expr(array->node.array_type_decl.size_expr)) {
8187 cod_src_error(context, array,
8188 "Array size expression must be constant.");
8189 return 0;
8190 }
8191 if (semanticize_expr(context,
8192 array->node.array_type_decl.size_expr, scope) == 0) {
8193 return 0;
8194 }
8195 } else {
8196 sm_ref element_ref = array->node.array_type_decl.element_ref;
8197 /* allow NULL array type sizes */
8198 if (element_ref->node_type != cod_declaration) {
8199 cod_src_error(context, element_ref,
8200 "Null sizes only allowed in parameter contexts");
8201 return 0;
8202 }
8203
8204 }
8205 dimen_p d = super_type->node.array_type_decl.dimensions;
8206 d->dimen_count++;
8207 d = realloc(d, sizeof(*d) + (sizeof(d->dimens[0]) * d->dimen_count));
8208 d->dimens[d->dimen_count].control_field = NULL((void*)0);
8209 super_type->node.array_type_decl.dimensions = d;
8210
8211 if (array->node.array_type_decl.element_ref->node_type
8212 == cod_declaration) {
8213 /* we're the last in line */
8214 sm_ref typ = NULL((void*)0);
8215 int cg_type = DILL_ERR;
8216 int ret;
8217 sm_ref decl = array->node.array_type_decl.element_ref;
8218 decl->node.declaration.sm_complex_type = super_type;
8219 decl->node.declaration.cg_type = DILL_B;
8220 ret = semanticize_decl(context, decl, scope);
8221 if (ret == 0) return 0;
8222
8223 if (decl->node.declaration.type_spec != NULL((void*)0)) {
8224 typ = reduce_type_list(context, decl->node.declaration.type_spec,
8225 &cg_type, scope, NULL((void*)0), &decl->node.declaration.freeable_complex_type);
8226 } else {
8227 sm_ref arr = decl->node.declaration.sm_complex_type;
8228 if ((arr != NULL((void*)0)) &&
8229 (arr->node_type == cod_array_type_decl)) {
8230 typ = reduce_type_list(context,
8231 arr->node.array_type_decl.type_spec,
8232 &cg_type, scope, NULL((void*)0), &decl->node.declaration.freeable_complex_type);
8233 }
8234 }
8235 if ((typ == NULL((void*)0)) && (cg_type == DILL_ERR)) return 0;
8236 array->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_type = cg_type;
8237 array->node.array_type_decl.sm_complex_element_type = typ;
8238 super_type->node.array_type_decl.cg_element_type = cg_type;
8239 } else {
8240 assert(array->node.array_type_decl.element_ref->node_type == cod_array_type_decl)((void) sizeof ((array->node.array_type_decl.element_ref->
node_type == cod_array_type_decl) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if
(array->node.array_type_decl.element_ref->node_type ==
cod_array_type_decl) ; else __assert_fail ("array->node.array_type_decl.element_ref->node_type == cod_array_type_decl"
, "cod/cod.y", 5975, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
8241 array->node.array_type_decl.sm_complex_element_type = array->node.array_type_decl.element_ref;
8242 return semanticize_array_element_node(context,
8243 array->node.array_type_decl.element_ref,
8244 array,
8245 base_type_spec, scope);
8246 }
8247 return 1;
8248}
8249
8250static int
8251semanticize_array_type_node(context, array, scope)
8252cod_parse_context context;
8253sm_ref array;
8254scope_ptr scope;
8255{
8256 if (!array->node.array_type_decl.dimensions) {
8257 array->node.array_type_decl.dimensions = malloc(sizeof(dimen_s));
8258 memset(array->node.array_type_decl.dimensions, 0, sizeof(dimen_s));
8259 }
8260 array->node.array_type_decl.dimensions->dimen_count = 0;
8261 return semanticize_array_element_node(context, array, array,
8262 array->node.array_type_decl.type_spec,
8263 scope);
8264}

8266#define Max(i,j)((i<j) ? j : i) ((i<j) ? j : i)
8267
8268extern FMTypeDesc*
8269gen_FMTypeDesc(FMFieldList fl, int field, const char *typ);
8270
8271static void
8272free_FMTypeDesc(FMTypeDesc *desc)
8273{
8274 while (desc) {
8275 FMTypeDesc *tmp = desc->next;
8276 free(desc);
8277 desc = tmp;
8278 }
8279 return;
8280}
8281
8282static int
8283semanticize_struct_type_node(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref decl,
8284 scope_ptr scope)
8285{
8286 FMFieldList fl = malloc(sizeof(fl[0]));
8287 int field_num = 0;
8288 int ret = 1;
8289 int struct_size = 0;
8290 sm_list fields = decl->node.struct_type_decl.fields;
8291 add_decl_ns(decl->node.struct_type_decl.id, decl, scope, NS_STRUCT);
8292 while(fields != NULL((void*)0)) {
8293 field *f = &fields->node->node.field;
8294 fl[field_num].field_name = f->name;
8295 fl[field_num].field_type = f->string_type;
8296 fl = realloc(fl, sizeof(fl[0]) * (field_num + 2));
8297 field_num++;
8298 fields = fields->next;
8299 }
8300 fl[field_num].field_name = NULL((void*)0);
8301 fl[field_num].field_type = NULL((void*)0);
8302 field_num = 0;
8303 fields = decl->node.struct_type_decl.fields;
8304 while(fields != NULL((void*)0)) {
8305 field *f = &fields->node->node.field;
8306 int err = 0;
8307 int field_size = f->cg_size;
8308
8309 if (f->string_type != NULL((void*)0)) {
8310 /* FFS-compatible field type */
8311 FMTypeDesc* desc = gen_FMTypeDesc(fl, field_num, f->string_type);
8312 if (desc == NULL((void*)0)) {
8313 cod_src_error(context, decl,
8314 "Field \"%s\" has unknown type \"%s\".",
8315 f->name, f->string_type);
8316 ret = 0;
8317 }
8318 build_type_nodes(context, decl, f, fields, f->cg_size, f->cg_type,
8319 desc, &err, scope);
8320
8321 free_FMTypeDesc(desc);
8322 f->cg_type = str_to_data_type(f->string_type, f->cg_size);
8323 field_size = f->cg_size;
8324 if (f->sm_complex_type) {
8325 if (f->sm_complex_type->node_type == cod_reference_type_decl) {
8326 field_size = sizeof(char*);
8327 } else if (f->sm_complex_type->node_type == cod_array_type_decl) {
8328 sm_ref arr = f->sm_complex_type;
8329 while (arr && (arr->node_type == cod_array_type_decl)) {
8330 if (arr->node.array_type_decl.cg_static_size != -1) {
8331 field_size *= arr->node.array_type_decl.cg_static_size;
8332 }
8333 arr = arr->node.array_type_decl.sm_complex_element_type;
8334 }
8335 }
8336 }
8337 } else {
8338 /* not able to get a FFS-compatible form */
8339 int type_def = 0;
8340 int cg_type;
8341 sm_ref typ;
8342 typ = reduce_type_list(context, f->type_spec, &cg_type, scope,
8343 &type_def, &f->freeable_complex_type);
8344 f->sm_complex_type = typ;
8345 f->cg_type = cg_type;
8346 field_size = -1;
8347 }
8348 if (err == 1) ret = 0;
8349 struct_size = Max(struct_size,((struct_size<(f->cg_offset + field_size)) ? (f->cg_offset
+ field_size) : struct_size)
8350 (f->cg_offset + field_size))((struct_size<(f->cg_offset + field_size)) ? (f->cg_offset
+ field_size) : struct_size);
8351 fields = fields->next;
8352 field_num++;
8353 }
8354 free(fl);
8355 decl->node.struct_type_decl.cg_size = struct_size;
8356 return ret;
8357}

8359static int
8360semanticize_enum_type_node(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref decl,
8361 scope_ptr scope)
8362{
8363 sm_list enums = decl->node.enum_type_decl.enums;
8364 int value = 0;
8365 while(enums != NULL((void*)0)) {
8366 if (enums->node->node.enumerator.const_expression) {
8367 if (!is_constant_expr(enums->node->node.enumerator.const_expression)) {
8368 cod_src_error(context, enums->node,
8369 "Enumerator value expression must be constant.");
8370 return 0;
8371 }
8372 }
8373 add_decl(enums->node->node.enumerator.id, enums->node, context->scope);
8374 enums = enums->next;
8375 }
8376 add_decl_ns(decl->node.enum_type_decl.id, decl, scope, NS_ENUM);
8377 return 1;
8378}

8386 add_decl(decl->node.reference_type_decl.name, decl, scope);
8387 }

8389}

8391extern sm_ref
8392cod_build_param_node(const char *id, sm_ref typ, int param_num)
8393{
8394 sm_ref node = cod_new_declaration();
8395 sm_ref ident;
8396 node->node.declaration.param_num = param_num;
8397 node->node.declaration.id = strdup(id);
8398 node->node.declaration.sm_complex_type = typ;
8399 if (typ != NULL((void*)0)) {
8400 ident = cod_new_identifier();
8401 node->node.declaration.type_spec = malloc(sizeof(struct list_struct));
8402 node->node.declaration.type_spec->next = NULL((void*)0);
8403 node->node.declaration.type_spec->node = ident;
8404 ident->node.identifier.id = strdup(typ->node.struct_type_decl.id);
8405 }
8406 return node;
8407}
8408
8409extern
8410void
8411get_FMformat_characteristics(FMFormat format, FMfloat_format *ff, FMinteger_format *intf, int *column_major, int *pointer_size);
8412
8413static
8414sm_ref cod_build_type_node_FMformat(FMFormat format, cod_parse_context context)
8415{
8416 sm_ref decl = cod_new_struct_type_decl();
8417 sm_list *end_ptr = &decl->node.struct_type_decl.fields;
8418 FMfloat_format data_float;
8419 FMinteger_format data_int;
8420 int column_major;
8421 int pointer_size;
8422 FMFieldList field_list = format->field_list;
8423 get_FMformat_characteristics(format, &data_float, &data_int, &column_major, &pointer_size);
8424
8425 decl->node.struct_type_decl.id = strdup(name_of_FMformat(format));
8426 decl->node.struct_type_decl.encode_info = malloc(sizeof(struct enc_struct));
8427 decl->node.struct_type_decl.encode_info->byte_order = data_int;
8428 decl->node.struct_type_decl.encode_info->float_order = data_float;
8429 decl->node.struct_type_decl.encode_info->pointer_size = pointer_size;
8430 while ((field_list != NULL((void*)0)) && (field_list->field_name != NULL((void*)0))) {
8431 sm_list new_elem;
8432 char *colon = strchr(field_list->field_type, ':');
8433 char *bracket = strchr(field_list->field_type, '[');
8434
8435 if (colon != NULL((void*)0)) {
8436 *colon = 0;
8437 if (bracket != NULL((void*)0)) strcpy(colon, bracket);
8438 }
8439 new_elem = malloc(sizeof(*new_elem));
8440 new_elem->next = NULL((void*)0);
8441 new_elem->node = cod_new_field();
8442 new_elem->node->node.field.name = strdup(field_list->field_name);
8443 new_elem->node->node.field.string_type = strdup(field_list->field_type);
8444 new_elem->node->node.field.cg_size = field_list->field_size;
8445 new_elem->node->node.field.cg_offset = field_list->field_offset;
8446 new_elem->node->node.field.cg_type = DILL_ERR;
8447 *end_ptr = new_elem;
8448 end_ptr = &new_elem->next;
8449 field_list++;
8450 }
8451 return decl;
8452}
8453
8454extern void
8455cod_add_encoded_param(const char *id, char *data, int param_num,
8456 FMContext c, cod_parse_context context)
8457{
8458 int i = 0;
8459 FMFormat format = FMformat_from_ID(c, data);
8460 FMFormat *formats;
8461 sm_ref top_type = NULL((void*)0), param_node;
8462 sm_ref node;
8463 if (format == NULL((void*)0)) {
8464 printf("No FMFormat ID found in buffer supplied to cod_add_encoded_param()\n");
8465 printf("No parameter added\n");
8466 return;
8467 }
8468 formats = format->subformats;
8469 while (formats[i] != NULL((void*)0)) {
8470 node = cod_build_type_node_FMformat(formats[i], context);
8471 cod_add_decl_to_parse_context(name_of_FMformat(formats[i]), node, context);
8472 cod_add_decl_to_scope(name_of_FMformat(formats[i]), node, context);
8473 top_type = node;
8474 i++;
8475 }
8476
8477 node = cod_build_type_node_FMformat(format, context);
8478 cod_add_decl_to_parse_context(name_of_FMformat(format), node, context);
8479 cod_add_decl_to_scope(name_of_FMformat(format), node, context);
8480 top_type = node;
8481 param_node = cod_build_param_node(id, NULL((void*)0), param_num);
8482 param_node->node.declaration.sm_complex_type = top_type;
8483 cod_add_decl_to_parse_context(id, param_node, context);
8484}
8485
8486extern void
8487cod_add_param(const char *id, const char *typ, int param_num,
8488 cod_parse_context context)
8489{
8490 sm_list type_list;
8491 sm_ref node;
8492 setup_for_string_parse(typ, context->defined_types, context->enumerated_constants);
8493 cod_code_string = typ;
8494 parsing_type = 1;
8495 yyerror_count = 0;
8496 yycontext = context;
8497 yyparsecod_yyparse();
8498 parsing_type = 0;
8499 terminate_string_parse();
8500
8501 if ((yyparse_value == NULL((void*)0)) || (yyerror_count != 0)) {
8502 return;
8503 }
8504 type_list = (sm_list) yyparse_value;
8505
8506 node = cod_build_param_node(id, NULL((void*)0), param_num);
8507 node->node.declaration.type_spec = type_list;
8508 cod_add_decl_to_parse_context(id, node, context);
8509}
8510
8511extern void
8512cod_subroutine_declaration(const char *decl, cod_parse_context context)
8513{
8514 sm_list type_list, params;
8515 sm_ref complex_type, declaration, freeable_complex_type = NULL((void*)0);
8516 int cg_type, param_num;
8517
8518 setup_for_string_parse(decl, context->defined_types, context->enumerated_constants);
8519 cod_code_string = decl;
8520 parsing_param_spec = 1;
8521 yyerror_count = 0;
8522 yycontext = context;
8523 yyparsecod_yyparse();
8524 parsing_param_spec = 0;
8525 terminate_string_parse();
8526
8527 if ((yyparse_value == NULL((void*)0)) || (yyerror_count != 0)) {
8528 return;
8529 }
8530 declaration = yyparse_value;
8531 context->freeable_declaration = declaration;
8532 type_list = declaration->node.declaration.type_spec;
8533
8534 /* handle return type */
8535 complex_type = reduce_type_list(context, type_list, &cg_type, context->scope, NULL((void*)0), &freeable_complex_type);
8536 if (freeable_complex_type) cod_rfree(freeable_complex_type);
8537 /* context->return_type_list = type_list; - Free'd as part of parse, not here*/
8538 if (complex_type != NULL((void*)0)) {
8539 cg_type = DILL_P;
8540 }
8541 context->return_cg_type = cg_type;
8542
8543 /* handle params */
8544 params = declaration->node.declaration.params;
8545 param_num = 0;
8546 while (params != NULL((void*)0)) {
8547 sm_ref param = NULL((void*)0);
8548 switch (params->node->node_type) {
8549 case cod_declaration:
8550 param = params->node;
8551 break;
8552 case cod_array_type_decl:
8553 param = params->node->node.array_type_decl.element_ref;
8554 param->node.declaration.sm_complex_type = params->node;
8555 break;
8556 default:
8557 printf("unhandled case in cod_subroutine_declaration\n");
8558 }
8559 param->node.declaration.param_num = param_num;
8560 cod_add_decl_to_parse_context(param->node.declaration.id,
8561 cod_copy(params->node), context);
8562 param_num++;
8563 params = params->next;
8564 }
8565}
8566
8567extern void
8568cod_set_return_type(char *typ, cod_parse_context context)
8569{
8570 sm_list type_list;
8571 int cg_type;
8572 sm_ref complex_type, freeable_complex_type = NULL((void*)0);
8573 setup_for_string_parse(typ, context->defined_types, context->enumerated_constants);
8574 cod_code_string = typ;
8575 parsing_type = 1;
8576 yyerror_count = 0;
8577 yycontext = context;
8578 yyparsecod_yyparse();
8579 parsing_type = 0;
8580 terminate_string_parse();
8581
8582 if ((yyparse_value == NULL((void*)0)) || (yyerror_count != 0)) {
8583 return;
8584 }
8585 type_list = (sm_list) yyparse_value;
8586
8587 complex_type = reduce_type_list(context, type_list, &cg_type, context->scope, NULL((void*)0), &freeable_complex_type);
8588 context->return_type_list = type_list;
8589 if (complex_type != NULL((void*)0)) {
8590 cg_type = DILL_P;
8591 if (freeable_complex_type) cod_rfree(freeable_complex_type);
8592 }
8593 context->return_cg_type = cg_type;
8594}

8596static sm_ref
8597find_complex_type(sm_ref node, scope_ptr scope)
8598{
8599 assert(node->node_type == cod_identifier)((void) sizeof ((node->node_type == cod_identifier) ? 1 : 0
), __extension__ ({ if (node->node_type == cod_identifier)
; else __assert_fail ("node->node_type == cod_identifier"
, "cod/cod.y", 6334, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
8600 return resolve(node->node.identifier.id, scope);
8601}
8602
8603extern cod_parse_context
8604new_cod_parse_context()
8605{
8606 cod_parse_context context = malloc(sizeof(struct parse_struct));
8607 context->decls = NULL((void*)0);
8608 context->standard_decls = NULL((void*)0);
8609 context->scope = push_scope(NULL((void*)0));
8610 context->defined_types = NULL((void*)0);
8611 context->enumerated_constants = NULL((void*)0);
8612 context->error_func = default_error_out;
8613 context->client_data = NULL((void*)0);
8614 context->return_type_list = NULL((void*)0);
8615 context->return_cg_type = DILL_I;
8616 context->freeable_declaration = NULL((void*)0);
8617 context->has_exec_context = 0;
8618 context->dont_coerce_return = 0;
8619 context->alloc_globals = 0;
8620 cod_add_standard_elements(context);
8621 return context;
8622}
8623
8624extern void
8625cod_free_parse_context(cod_parse_context parse_context)
8626{
8627 if (parse_context->scope->externs) {
8628 int i = 0;
8629 while(parse_context->scope->externs[i].extern_name) {
8630 free(parse_context->scope->externs[i].extern_name);
8631 i++;
8632 }
8633 free(parse_context->scope->externs);
8634 }
8635 pop_scope(parse_context->scope);
8636 if (parse_context->defined_types) {
8637 free(parse_context->defined_types);
8638 }
8639 if (parse_context->decls) {
8640 cod_rfree_list(parse_context->decls, NULL((void*)0));
8641 }
8642 if (parse_context->return_type_list) {
8643 cod_rfree_list(parse_context->return_type_list, NULL((void*)0));
8644 }
8645 if (parse_context->standard_decls) {
8646 cod_rfree_list(parse_context->standard_decls, NULL((void*)0));
8647 }
8648 if (parse_context->freeable_declaration) {
8649 cod_rfree(parse_context->freeable_declaration);
8650 }
8651 free(parse_context);
8652}
8653
8654extern void
8655cod_assoc_externs(cod_parse_context context, cod_extern_list externs)
8656{
8657 int new_count = 0;
8658
8659 while(externs[new_count].extern_value) new_count++;
8660
8661 if (context->scope->externs == NULL((void*)0)) {
8662 int i;
8663 context->scope->externs = malloc((new_count+1) * sizeof(externs[0]));
8664 for (i=0; i < new_count; i++) {
8665 context->scope->externs[i].extern_name = strdup(externs[i].extern_name);
8666 context->scope->externs[i].extern_value = externs[i].extern_value;
8667 }
8668 context->scope->externs[new_count].extern_name = NULL((void*)0);
8669 context->scope->externs[new_count].extern_value = NULL((void*)0);
8670 } else {
8671 int old_count = 0;
8672 int i;
8673 while(context->scope->externs[old_count++].extern_value);
8674 context->scope->externs = realloc(context->scope->externs, (new_count + old_count) * sizeof(externs[0]));
8675
8676 for (i=0; i < new_count; i++) {
8677 int j;
8678 for (j=0; j < old_count-1; j++) {
8679 if (strcmp(externs[i].extern_name, context->scope->externs[j].extern_name) == 0) {
8680 context->scope->externs[j].extern_value = externs[i].extern_value;
8681 }
8682 }
8683 context->scope->externs[old_count + i - 1].extern_name = strdup(externs[i].extern_name);
8684 context->scope->externs[old_count + i - 1].extern_value = externs[i].extern_value;
8685 }
8686 context->scope->externs[new_count + old_count -1].extern_name = NULL((void*)0);
8687 context->scope->externs[new_count + old_count -1].extern_value = NULL((void*)0);
8688 }
8689}

8691extern void
8692cod_add_decl_to_parse_context(const char *name, sm_ref item, cod_parse_context context)
8693{
8694 sm_list *last_ptr = &context->decls;
8695 sm_list list = context->decls;
8696 while (list != NULL((void*)0)) {
8697 last_ptr = &list->next;
8698 list = list->next;
8699 }
8700 *last_ptr = malloc(sizeof(*list));
8701 (*last_ptr)->next = NULL((void*)0);
8702 (*last_ptr)->node = item;
8703 if (item->node_type == cod_struct_type_decl) {
8704 cod_add_defined_type((char *)name, context);
8705 }
8706}

8708extern void
8709cod_add_int_constant_to_parse_context(const char *const_name, int value, cod_parse_context context)

8717 constant->node.constant.const_val = strdup(str_value);
8718 constant->node.constant.freeable_name = name;
8719 cod_add_decl_to_scope((char*) name, constant, context);
8720 cod_add_decl_to_parse_context(name, constant, context);
8721}

) ; else __assert_fail ("decl->node_type == cod_declaration"

: 0), __extension__ ({ if (decl->node.declaration.is_subroutine
) ; else __assert_fail ("decl->node.declaration.is_subroutine"

8732
8733static void
8734space_to_underscore(char *str){
8735 while(*str != '\0'){
8736 if(isspace(*str)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((*str))] & (unsigned short int
) _ISspace))
8737 *str = '_';
8738 str++;
8739 }
8740}
8741
8742static void
8743purify_name(FMStructDescList list){
8744 int i,j;
8745 for(i=0; list[i].format_name; i++){
8746 FMFieldList fl = list[i].field_list;
8747 space_to_underscore((char*)list[i].format_name);
8748 for(j=0; fl[j].field_name; j++){
8749 space_to_underscore((char*)fl[j].field_name);
8750 space_to_underscore((char*)fl[j].field_type);
8751 }
8752 }
8753}
8754
8755static void
8756uniqueify_names(FMStructDescList list, char *prefix)
8757{
8758 int i = 0;
8759 int prefix_len = strlen(prefix);
8760 while (list[i].format_name != NULL((void*)0)) {
8761 int j = 0;
8762 FMFieldList fl = list[i].field_list;
8763 char *new_name =
8764 malloc(strlen(list[i].format_name) + prefix_len + 1);
8765 strcpy(new_name, prefix);
8766 strcpy(new_name + prefix_len, list[i].format_name);
8767 free(list[i].format_name);
8768 list[i].format_name = new_name;
8769 while (fl[j].field_name != 0) {
8770 int field_type_len = strlen(fl[j].field_type);
8771 char *bracket = strchr(fl[j].field_type, '[');
8772 int k;
8773 if (bracket != NULL((void*)0)) {
8774 field_type_len = (long) bracket - (long) fl[j].field_type;
8775 }
8776 for (k = 0; k < i; k++) {
8777 char *new_type;
8778 if (strncmp
8779 (fl[j].field_type, list[k].format_name + prefix_len,
8780 field_type_len) != 0) {
8781 /* don't match in N chars */
8782 continue;
8783 }
8784 if ((list[k].format_name + prefix_len)[field_type_len] !=
8785 0) {
8786 /* list name is longer */
8787 continue;
8788 }
8789 new_type =
8790 malloc(strlen(fl[j].field_type) + prefix_len + 1);
8791 strcpy(new_type, prefix);
8792 strcpy(new_type + prefix_len, fl[j].field_type);
8793 free((void *) fl[j].field_type);
8794 fl[j].field_type = new_type;
8795 break;
8796 }
8797 j++;
8798 }
8799 i++;
8800 }
8801 purify_name(list);
8802}
8803
8804/* Returns the ecode function which will do message format conversion */
8805extern cod_code
8806gen_rollback_code(FMStructDescList format1, FMStructDescList format2, char *xform_code)
8807{
8808 /* setup ECL generation */
8809 /*
8810 * NOTE: We have to make the type names (structure names)
8811 * in format1 and format2 to be unique.
8812 * Because of the nature of the problem, they are likely to be
8813 * identical and this may cause namespace collisions in ECL.
8814 */
8815 cod_code code;
8816 cod_parse_context parse_context = new_cod_parse_context();
8817
8818 int i = 0;
8819 uniqueify_names(format1, "f0_");
8820 while (format1[i].format_name != NULL((void*)0)) {
8821 cod_add_simple_struct_type(format1[i].format_name,
8822 format1[i].field_list, parse_context);
8823 i++;
8824 }
8825 cod_add_param("new", format1[i - 1].format_name, 0, parse_context);
8826
8827 i = 0;
8828 uniqueify_names(format2, "f1_");
8829 while (format2[i].format_name != NULL((void*)0)) {
8830 cod_add_simple_struct_type(format2[i].format_name,
8831 format2[i].field_list, parse_context);
8832 i++;
8833 }
8834 cod_add_param("old", format2[i - 1].format_name, 1, parse_context);
8835
8836 code = cod_code_gen(xform_code, parse_context);
8837 cod_free_parse_context(parse_context);
8838
8839 /*
8840 * the "code" structure is the only output from this block,
8841 * all else is free'd.
8842 */
8843 return code;
8844}
8845
8846static double
8847get_constant_float_value(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref expr)
8848{
8849 double result;
8850 switch(expr->node.constant.token) {
8851 case integer_constant:
8852 case floating_constant:
8853 sscanf(expr->node.constant.const_val, "%lg", &result);
8854 return result;
8855 case string_constant:
8856 return 0.0;
8857 case character_constant:
8858 return (double)(unsigned char)expr->node.constant.const_val[0];
8859 default:
8860 assert(FALSE)((void) sizeof ((0) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (0) ; else __assert_fail
("FALSE", "cod/cod.y", 6595, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); }));
8861 }
8862}
8863
8864static long
8865get_constant_long_value(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref expr)
8866{
8867 double dresult;
8868 long result;
8869 switch(expr->node.constant.token) {
8870 case integer_constant:
8871 sscanf(expr->node.constant.const_val, "%ld", &result);
8872 return result;
8873 case floating_constant:
8874 sscanf(expr->node.constant.const_val, "%lg", &dresult);
8875 return (long)dresult;
8876 case string_constant:
8877 return -1;
8878 case character_constant:
8879 return (long)(unsigned char)expr->node.constant.const_val[0];
8880 default:
8881 assert(FALSE)((void) sizeof ((0) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (0) ; else __assert_fail
("FALSE", "cod/cod.y", 6616, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); }));
8882 }
8883}
8884
8885extern sm_ref
8886evaluate_constant_return_expr(cod_parse_context context, sm_ref expr, int *free_result)
8887{
8888 switch(expr->node_type) {
8889 case cod_constant:
8890 *free_result = 0;
8891 return expr;
8892 case cod_identifier:
8893 return evaluate_constant_return_expr(context, expr->node.identifier.sm_declaration, free_result);
8894 case cod_declaration:
8895 if (!expr->node.declaration.const_var) return NULL((void*)0);
8896 return evaluate_constant_return_expr(context, expr->node.identifier.sm_declaration, free_result);
8897 case cod_operator: {
8898 sm_ref left = NULL((void*)0), right = NULL((void*)0), ret;
8899 int free_left = 0, free_right = 0;
8900 int left_token, right_token;
8901 if (expr->node.operator.left != NULL((void*)0)) {
8902 if (!(left = evaluate_constant_return_expr(context, expr->node.operator.left, &free_left))) return NULL((void*)0);
8903 left_token = left->node.constant.token;
8904 }
8905 if (expr->node.operator.op == op_sizeof) {
8906 int cg_type;
8907 sm_ref cast = expr->node.operator.right;
8908 sm_ref typ;
8909 long size;
8910 assert(cast->node_type == cod_cast)((void) sizeof ((cast->node_type == cod_cast) ? 1 : 0), __extension__
({ if (cast->node_type == cod_cast) ; else __assert_fail (
"cast->node_type == cod_cast", "cod/cod.y", 6645, __extension__
__PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
8911 typ = reduce_type_list(context, cast->node.cast.type_spec, &cg_type, context? context->scope:NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
8912 static dill_stream s = NULL((void*)0);
8913 char str_val[40];
8914 extern int cg_get_size(dill_stream s, sm_ref node);
8915
8916 if (s == NULL((void*)0)) {
8917 s = dill_create_stream();
8918 }
8919 if (typ == NULL((void*)0)) {
8920 size = dill_type_size(s, cg_type)s->j->type_size[cg_type];
8921 } else {
8922 size = cg_get_size(s, cast);
8923 }
8924 ret = cod_new_constant();
8925 ret->node.constant.token = integer_constant;
8926 sprintf(str_val, "%ld", size);
8927 ret->node.constant.const_val = strdup(str_val);
8928 *free_result = 1;
8929 return ret;
8930 }
8931 if (expr->node.operator.right != NULL((void*)0)) {
8932 if (!(right = evaluate_constant_return_expr(context, expr->node.operator.right, &free_right))) return NULL((void*)0);
8933 right_token = right->node.constant.token;
8934 if (!expr->node.operator.left) {
8935 left_token = right_token;
8936 }
8937 }
8938 if ((left_token == string_constant) ||
8939 (right_token == string_constant)) {
8940 /* blech. No operators on strings. */
8941 return NULL((void*)0);
8942 }
8943 if ((left_token == floating_constant) ||
8944 (right_token == floating_constant)) {
8945 double left_val, right_val, fvalue;
8946 int ivalue, is_ivalue = 0;
8947 char str_val[40];
8948 if (left)
8949 left_val = get_constant_float_value(context, left);
8950 if (right)
8951 right_val = get_constant_float_value(context, right);
8952 switch(expr->node.operator.op) {
8953 case op_plus:
8954 fvalue = left_val + right_val;
8955 break;
8956 case op_minus:
8957 fvalue = left_val - right_val;
8958 break;
8959 case op_leq:
8960 ivalue = left_val <= right_val;
8961 is_ivalue=1;
8962 break;
8963 case op_lt:
8964 ivalue = left_val < right_val;
8965 is_ivalue=1;
8966 break;
8967 case op_geq:
8968 ivalue = left_val >= right_val;
8969 is_ivalue=1;
8970 break;
8971 case op_gt:
8972 ivalue = left_val > right_val;
8973 is_ivalue=1;
8974 break;
8975 case op_eq:
8976 ivalue = left_val = right_val;
8977 is_ivalue=1;
8978 break;
8979 case op_neq:
8980 ivalue = left_val != right_val;
8981 is_ivalue=1;
8982 break;
8983 case op_mult:
8984 fvalue = left_val * right_val;
8985 break;
8986 case op_div:
8987 if (right_val == 0) {
8988 return NULL((void*)0);
8989 }
8990 fvalue = left_val / right_val;
8991 break;
8992 case op_log_neg:
8993 case op_not:
8994 case op_left_shift:
8995 case op_right_shift:
8996 case op_modulus:
8997 case op_log_or:
8998 case op_arith_or:
8999 case op_arith_xor:
9000 case op_log_and:
9001 case op_arith_and:
9002 case op_deref:
9003 case op_address:
9004 case op_inc:
9005 case op_dec:
9006 case op_sizeof:
9007 assert(FALSE)((void) sizeof ((0) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (0) ; else __assert_fail
("FALSE", "cod/cod.y", 6742, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); }));
9008 }
9009 ret = cod_new_constant();
9010 if (is_ivalue) {
9011 ret->node.constant.token = integer_constant;
9012 sprintf(str_val, "%d", ivalue);
9013 } else {
9014 ret->node.constant.token = floating_constant;
9015 sprintf(str_val, "%.*e\n", OP_DBL_Digs(17) - 1, fvalue);
9016 }
9017 ret->node.constant.const_val = strdup(str_val);
9018 *free_result = 1;
9019 } else {
9020 /* we get an integer result */
9021 long left_val = 0, right_val = 0, value;
9022 char str_val[40];
9023 if (expr->node.operator.left)
9024 left_val = get_constant_long_value(context, left);
9025 if (expr->node.operator.right)
9026 right_val = get_constant_long_value(context, right);
9027 switch(expr->node.operator.op) {
9028 case op_modulus:
9029 if (right_val == 0) {
9030 return NULL((void*)0);
9031 }
9032 value = left_val % right_val;
9033 break;
9034 case op_plus:
9035 value = left_val + right_val;
9036 break;
9037 case op_minus:
9038 value = left_val - right_val;
9039 break;
9040 case op_leq:
9041 value = left_val <= right_val;
9042 break;
9043 case op_lt:
9044 value = left_val < right_val;
9045 break;
9046 case op_geq:
9047 value = left_val >= right_val;
9048 break;
9049 case op_gt:
9050 value = left_val > right_val;
9051 break;
9052 case op_eq:
9053 value = left_val = right_val;
9054 break;
9055 case op_neq:
9056 value = left_val != right_val;
9057 break;
9058 case op_log_or:
9059 value = left_val || right_val;
9060 break;
9061 case op_arith_or:
9062 value = left_val | right_val;
9063 break;
9064 case op_arith_xor:
9065 value = left_val ^ right_val;
9066 break;
9067 case op_log_and:
9068 value = left_val && right_val;
9069 break;
9070 case op_arith_and:
9071 value = left_val & right_val;
9072 break;
9073 case op_mult:
9074 value = left_val * right_val;
9075 break;
9076 case op_div:
9077 value = left_val / right_val;
9078 break;
9079 case op_log_neg:
9080 value = !right_val;
9081 break;
9082 case op_not:
9083 value = ~right_val;
9084 break;
9085 case op_left_shift:
9086 value = left_val << right_val;
9087 break;
9088 case op_right_shift:
9089 value = left_val >> right_val;
9090 break;
9091 case op_deref:
9092 case op_address:
9093 case op_inc:
9094 case op_dec:
9095 case op_sizeof:
9096 assert(FALSE)((void) sizeof ((0) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (0) ; else __assert_fail
